(1262, 2454806, 2454806, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Voices Rising ', 'VOICES RISING &lt;br /&gt;AN EVENING OF EMERGING YOUNG QUEER ARTISTS OF COLOR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;@ &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;Langston Hughes&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;Performing Arts Center&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;104 - 17th Ave. South (at Yesler) &lt;span&gt;Seattle WA 98144&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;Friday December 5, 2008.   8pm&lt;/span&gt; (Doors open at &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;7:30pm&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;$10-25 sliding scale. Available at &lt;span&gt;Brown Paper Tickets&lt;/span&gt; &amp; at the door.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Voices Rising, a showcase dedicated solely to LGBTQ artists of color, hosts an&lt;br /&gt;evening of powerful performances by five emerging artists under 25.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Returning to the Voices Rising stage is the lyrical jazz/hip hop duo&lt;br /&gt;THEESatisfaction. They&#039;re joined by Seattle&#039;s fiercest up-and-coming young&lt;br /&gt;artists including Justin Huertas, Mikeya Jackson-Harper, Landon Longhill, and&lt;br /&gt;Crystal Ybarra. This event is presented in partnership with the Langston Hughes&lt;br /&gt;Performing Arts Center, the &lt;span&gt;American Friends Service Committee&#039;s LGBT Peace&lt;/span&gt; and&lt;br /&gt;Social Justice Program, and Naomi Ishisaka. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(1263, 2454806, 2454806, '20:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'APHONIA RECORDINGS: series pt. 12 (w/ Derek M. Johnson, 1908, ..more) ', 'Aphonia Recordings Series #12 showcase:&lt;br /&gt;Friday, December 5th @ Gallery 1412&lt;br /&gt;(1412 18th ave - Seattle, WA)&lt;br /&gt;8:00PM&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Derek M. Johnson (Olympia)&lt;br /&gt;1908 (PDX)&lt;br /&gt;Baby Birds Don&#039;t Drink Milk (Lawrence, KS)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;DEREK M. JOHNSON&lt;br /&gt;Derek is an Olympia, WA native and can&#039;t seem to ever get away. He frequently performs solo acoustic/electric cello throughout the Northwest with an ever changing, direct animation slide show. He&#039;s been a member of Bloodclot, Dead Air Fresheners, Le Ton Mite, Frequency dB, and the unfortunately named Superfly 2000. Collaborations include: Unwound, Thollem McDonnas, Jeremy Jay, Ben L Robertson, Arrington de Dionyso, Bob Marsh, among others. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;1908&lt;br /&gt;1908 is a semi-improvisational, free-form, multi-instrumental, virtuosically-elctroacoustic, casually-cantankerous, zealously-unzealous, often-deplorable music project borne of Portland,&lt;br /&gt;Oregon.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;BABY BIRDS DON&#039;T DRINK MILK&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Psych-tinged (sometimes pop and sometimes folk) melodies with a shoegaze accent, occasional noisy interludes and an inclination for ambience never forgetting about late Seventies/early Eighties British new wave.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Best Kept Secret&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://aphoniarecordings.com&quot;&gt;www.aphoniarecordings.com&lt;/a&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(1264, 2454813, 2454813, '20:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Live Soundtrack to &quot;Phantom of the Opera&quot; (1929, Lon Cheney) w/ Derek M. Johnson, Rachel Carns, Heather Hall, Daniel Buscher ', 'PHANTOM OF THE OPERA (LIVE SOUNDTRACK)&lt;br /&gt;Friday, December 12th @ Gallery 1412&lt;br /&gt;(1412 18th Ave - Seattle, WA)&lt;br /&gt;8:00PM&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Silent 1929 film &quot;Phantom of the Opera,&quot; starring Lon Cheney (man of 1000 faces) and featuring a live soundtrack by Derek M. Johnson, Rachel Carns, Heather Hall, &amp; Daniel Buscher.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Following the successful performance at the 25th Olympia Film Festival, the group decided to do one last performance in Seattle at Gallery 1412 prior to releasing an edited record of our first performance on Aphonia Recordings.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Rachel Carns - Piano/Organ&lt;br /&gt;Rachel has lived in Olympia for 16 years &amp; done lots of stuff. She is currently a graphic designer by trade (under the nom des artes System Lux), master brewer at Magic Kombucha, &amp; plays in local band TWIN.  She&#039;s a former member of The Need and played drums for &quot;The Transfused&quot; punk rock opera.  Double Leo, Aquarius rising.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Heather Hall - electronics/misc percussion&lt;br /&gt;Her work ranges from acoustic/electronic noise and goofy transcendental performance to amplified cymbal ensemble drones. She has lived in Olympia for 5 years and currently attends The Evergreen State College for circuit design and music technology. Her interest in analog circuitry has led her attention to other more subtle energy systems within the healing arts. If you&#039;re a techno-shaman and need an apprentice, e-mail this lady at hall.arecibo@gmail.com.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Derek M. Johnson - acoustic/electric cello&lt;br /&gt;Derek is an Oly native and can&#039;t seem to ever get away.  He frequently performs solo acoustic/electric cello throughout the Northwest with an ever changing, direct animation slide show.  He&#039;s been a member of Bloodclot, Dead Air Fresheners, Le Ton Mite, Frequency dB, and the unfortunately named Superfly 2000.  Collaborations include: Unwound, Thollem McDonnas, Jeremy Jay, Ben L Robertson, Arrington de Dionyso, Bob Marsh, among others.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Daniel Buscher - flute/misc percussion&lt;br /&gt;Daniel Buscher is a flutist of international renown. He writes confessional poetry and flute dance jams under the name Daniel Dance.  Daniel is moving to Montreal to get a masters in flute so this will be our final performance.  sad but true  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://aphoniarecordings.com&quot;&gt;www.aphoniarecordings.com&lt;/a&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
