(45, 2454359, 2454359, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'The Bikery! ', '*Learn about your rights as a Biker and Women&#039;s History and Biking*&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;     Join the Bikery on Saturday, September 15th at the Garfield Community Center in Seattle&#039;s Central District for two great programs.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;     The first is a community discussion titled &quot;Know Your Rights&quot; from, 12-2pm. &quot;Know your rights&quot; will be a conversation-based workshop where you will have the opportunity to share war stories and survival skills, tackle long-unanswered questions, and much more. Together we will explore our options as cyclists through discussion of the law as its stands, as well as learning from each other&#039;s experiences.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;     Then from 3-5pm Emer McKenna will present a thorougly researched presentation on the history of women in biking. Join us for this exciting program where you will learn why Susan B. Anthony said. &quot;The bicycle has done more for the emancipation of women than anything else in the world&quot;.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;     From 2-5pm the Bikery will also be hosting its weekly free bicycle maintenance drop-in clinic. If your bike needs some work, just bring it by with any parts you need. We supply the tools, and our volunteers will teach you how to repair your bike. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[2X', ''),
