(83, 2454356, 2454356, '18:00:00', '19:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'Future of ZAPP Volunteer Meeting ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Do you love the ZINE ARCHIVE AND PUBLISHING PROJECT?? Do you want to make sure that it serves the zine community when it reopens in 2008? THE HUGO HOUSE NEEDS TO KNOW THAT THIS WEDNESDAY.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The MEETING will be in the cabaret space at 6pm at the Richard Hugo House, TOMORROW, WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 12TH.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The following is reprinted for an email sent by Alix Wilber, Programs Director for the Hugo House, sent to ZAPP&#039;s Volunteers. THAT &quot;VOLUNTEER EMAIL LIST&quot; IS NOT CURRENT since the computer with the updated email list was stolen. IF YOU HAVE EVER VOLUNTEERED AT ZAPP IN SOME CAPACITY, PLEASE COME TO THE MEETING AND SHOW YOUR SUPPORT.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;your friend and mine, n. adam beadel&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Dear ZAPP volunteers:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As many of you already know, ZAPP is on hiatus until early 2008. Until then the library will be closed to the public while we take stock and do inventory of the collection. We will start accepting new zines and resume other zine-related activities when we reopen next year.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;ZAPP is one of several programs at Richard Hugo House; as Program Director, I am ultimately responsible for looking at what is best for the organization as a whole, not just the interests of one particular program. In light of several programmatic and organizational difficulties that have arisen in ZAPP over the past year, I came to the conclusion that the current situation is not good for Hugo House or for ZAPP. As a result, and in consultation with our Executive Director, Lyall Bush, I&amp;rsquo;ve decided to temporarily shut the doors while we take a step back to consider where we are and where we want to go.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This doesn&amp;rsquo;t mean that ZAPP will go entirely dark in the meantime, however. Over the next few months, a committee consisting of Hugo House staff and interested members of the zine community will be working together to evaluate how best to preserve and share the archive, and then to set clear, realistic goals for the future. I am hopeful that the task of cataloging the collection will continue and that volunteers who are interested in helping with that task will continue to do so.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If any of you would like to meet with me in person to discuss ZAPP&amp;rsquo;s future and to share your ideas about it, I will be holding an open space meeting on Wednesday, September 12 from 6:00 until 7:00. I hope to see you all here.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Alix Wilber&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
