(201, 2454375, 2454405, '17:30:00', '00:00:00', 'Floating', 1, 'CRITICAL MASS! ', '&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Critical Mass!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Every last Friday of the month in over 100 cities around the world cyclists congregate and ride in demonstration and in celebration. Critical Mass has no leaders or set agenda. People come together to ride for many different reasons.&lt;br /&gt; Some of those reasons are:&lt;br /&gt;  To assert cyclists&#039; right to the road, to promote bikes as a fun, healthy, viable alternative to cars, to build a greater sense of community, to get more folks on bikes, or simply to celebrate bike love and ride in solidarity with other like minded individuals and have some fun!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Meet at Westlake Center at 5:30pm.&lt;br /&gt; or Red Square on UW Campus at 5pm. ', 0, 0, 0, 5, 5, '0[2X', ''),
(99, 2454378, 2454378, '18:00:00', '20:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'Mass Romantic - Free Screening &amp; Q&amp;A ', 'What: Mass Romantic, a new indie feature, screens at The L.I.N.K. Film Festival, followed by a Q&amp;A with director Richard Paro and members of the cast. With Mass Romantic in the very last stages of completion, Paro will make final adjustments to the film after this public screening and discussion.\r\nWhere: Olympia Free School, 601 Columbia Street, Comm. 1, Olympia, WA 98501\r\nAdmission: Free\r\nwww.mudgeonsoul.org, www.myspace.com/MassRomanticFilm\r\n\nMass Romantic follows activists and academics struggling to find love while creating political art. The film focuses on the character’s relationships, while touching on controversial topics such as healthcare, queer politics, abortion, transphobia, food activism and corporate control of media. The theme of coalition-building present in Mass Romantic is reflected by the diverse group of individuals involved in the making of the film, many of whom are underrepresented in American cinema and identify as women, LGBTQ, people of color, non-native speakers and/or activists. Paro, along with partner Cyra K. Polizzi, produced Mass Romantic with a DIY sensibility after extensive story development and workshopping, utilizing the creative input and improvisational skills of the cast. \r\nMass Romantic was shot in the sweltering Chicago heat of late summer in just 11 days featuring 40 actors in over 10 locations, producing 33 hours of footage. The film features 13 independent bands, including Seattle-based Coyote Grace and live performances by Carrie Lydon, Kate Brown, ROFO and members of Head of Femur. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
