(209, 2454417, 2454417, '18:00:00', '20:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Communities Confronting Globalization: Autonomy, Human Rights, and Resistance ', 'The Red de Defensores Comunitarios Por los Derechos Humanos (Community&lt;br /&gt;Network of Human Rights Defenders) is an alternative, autonomous model&lt;br /&gt;of human rights work in which community members who suffer human&lt;br /&gt;rights abuses at the hands of army, paramilitaries, and federal&lt;br /&gt;government assume control of their own defense.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;COME  JOIN US IN SEATTLE AT THE UW!!!!&lt;br /&gt;WHEN:  Monday NOVEMBER 12TH 6PM!&lt;br /&gt;WHERE:  Gould Hall, Room 440, University of Washington Seattle Campus&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An indigenous community member from Chiapas, Mexico will &lt;br /&gt;-discuss threats to indigenous communities, such as NAFTA, Plan Puebla Panama, and the agricultural crisis in Mexico.&lt;br /&gt;- Discuss human rights abuses in Mexico, their relationship to neoliberal globalization, and how indigenous communities are working to end the abuses and impunity.&lt;br /&gt;- Promote a sustainable model of international trade based on economic justice.&lt;br /&gt;- Discuss the leadership of women in fair trade cooperatives as another example of indigenous Zapatista communities exercising autonomy. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(210, 2454414, 2454414, '19:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Special screening of RiverWebs @UW ', 'special screening of RiverWebs (http://www.riverwebs.org)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#3300ff&quot;&gt;+ Post screening discussion w/ film&#039;s director Jeremy Monroe&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;Fri, Nov 9, 2007&lt;br /&gt;7:00pm&lt;br /&gt;102 Johnson Hall on the UW Seattle campus.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This documentary follows an unlikely circle of river ecologists through tragedy, growth, and recovery.&lt;br /&gt;RiverWebs brings a very human side to science, while demonstrating the process of new discoveries.&lt;br /&gt;FREE AND OPEN TO THE PUBLIC&lt;br /&gt;More information: Julian Olden olden AT u dot washington DOT edu ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(211, 2454428, 2454428, '12:30:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, '15th ANNUAL BUY NOTHING DAY! Downtown Zombie BIKE RIDE ', '&lt;br /&gt;25% of the world&#039;s population consumes over 80% of the world&#039;s material resources and owns over 80% of its wealth. &lt;br /&gt;Although people today are, on average, four-and-a-half times richer than our great-grandparents were at the turn of the century, Americans report feeling &quot;significantly less well off&quot; than in 1958.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is because in our empty consumer culture we are always told that we need just one more thing to be happy. As long as you are buying your happiness, it&#039;s always going to be just out of your reach, always one more purchase away.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come make a stand against this cycle!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will meet at Westlake Square (between 4th Ave. and 5th Ave. / between Pike and Pine) at 12:30pm and will leave around 1pm.  (Also, if you absolutely can&#039;t show up at this time, but would like to participate, we will be sticking around the downtown area, so COME DOWN ANYWAY!)&lt;br /&gt;Please come in your zombie garb and bring your bicycle.  We will ride in a slow moving, critical mass style swarm, through-out the busiest streets downtown.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I am still trying to work out the details of this, but I would like to have large BUY NOTHING patches, possibly screen printed from old T-Shirts, so that our purpose is apparent to traffic.  If you have skills / time to donate /  fabric / paint PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE get a hold of me.&lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;If you are interested in more information or if you have any ideas please feel to email me at &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:cancerous.enjoyment@gmail.com&quot;&gt;cancerous.enjoyment@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt; It would be great if you could put BUY NOTHING, or something of the sort in the subject line, so that I can actually sort through my junk mail!&lt;br /&gt;Alternately, give me a call after 5:30 pm M-F or ANYTIME on the weekend : 206.370.1737 &lt;br /&gt;Angela&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more information on what BND is all about, refer to the sites below.&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buy_Nothing_Dayhttp://adbusters.org/metas/eco/bnd/#take_the_plunge&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buy_Nothing_Day&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;http://adbusters.org/metas/eco/bnd/#take_the_plunge&lt;/a&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
(214, 2454415, 2454415, '20:00:00', '21:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'Restless Natives: An interactive performance project ', 'Held at Lighting Designs, Inc.,&lt;br /&gt;76 S. Washington st., Seattle.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An interactive performance involving dance (Bharatanatyam, a South Indian classical form, as well as some flamenco and other dance styles), poetry (original pieces as well as work by Emmanuel Ortiz, Howard Zinn, and Roberto Juarroz), and live music (all original, on Native American Flute, drum, and charango), relating to historical injustice, the instituion of warfare, children caught up in it, and individual and community relationship to society and how to change it. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(215, 2454422, 2454422, '14:00:00', '16:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Creating a Culture of Connection in Activist Communities: Tools for Sustainability &amp; Hope ', '&lt;strong&gt;WORKSHOP SATURDAY NOVEMBER 17TH&lt;br /&gt;  2-4 PM @ THE VERA PROJECT&lt;br /&gt;  $5-10 SUGGESTED DONATION&lt;br /&gt;  ~no one turned away for lack of funds~&lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;  CONNECT:&lt;/strong&gt; Jenna Goldin + Karen Hixson rctportland@gmail.com 503.820.9167&lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;strong&gt;CONNECT BIO:&lt;/strong&gt; Karen and Jenna have been working together for the past year to develop tools for the larger community to address issues of disconnection and isolation. They use communication and relational awareness to support healthy relationships and community. Their June 2007 workshop entitled &amp;ldquo;Disconnection and Burnout in Activist Communities: Tools for Sustainability and Hope&amp;rdquo; brought over 40 activists together to discuss these issues. They recently presented at the Psychology Ecology and Sustainability Conference at Lewis and Clark College and wrote an article entitled &amp;ldquo;Building a Culture of Connection as Activists&amp;rdquo;  for Herbivore Magazine. &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;strong&gt;FLIER: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://killingcupid.net/rctfliernov17.jpg&quot;&gt;click here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;DOWNLOADABLE, PRINTABLE PDF:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://killingcupid.net/rctfliernov17.pdf&quot;&gt;click here&lt;/a&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
