(276, 2454443, 2454443, '18:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'fundraiser fest for The Bike Shack!!! ', 'Come join us at the 1st annual Homebrew Festival/potluck/fundraiser at Casa Luna!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Who: You!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;What: Fundraiser for The Bike Shack; good food, great people, live music, at least a dozen different homebrews from several different brewers on tap and in bottles, as well as kombucha, ginger ale and root beer. Some of the more exotic beers include a two-year-old barleywine, a coconut curry hefeweizen, a winter squash/sweet potato ale, a chipotle pepper ale, and a mugwort imperial stout.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Where: Casa Luna Co-op, 7321 12th Avenue NE.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;When: Saturday, December 8th, from 6pm - 1am.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;How: There are a strict 100 invitations available, so buy your ticket now, they&#039;ll go fast! $10 gets you all of the drinks you can imbibe. We request that you bring your own favorite drinking glass, though glasses will be available there for a small fee. (No crappy disposable plastic cups!)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Designated drivers are highly encouraged to come, will get in for free, do not need their own invitation, and will get all of the nonalcoholic drinks they want. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Why: The Bike Shack is a community-run bicycle shop, where anyone is welcome to come in and work on bicycles or learn about bicycle mechanics. It is entirely run by volunteers, and is supported solely by peoples&#039; generous donations. Recently, the Wayward Cafe has started to charge rent for their garage space, which has placed a tremendous financial burden on the Shack. Additionally, the garage was broken into over the summer, and several expensive tools were stolen. The goal of the fundraiser is to generate enough revenue to replace the stolen tools, and hopefully provide some money for rent for the near future. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;People can buy their tickets from me or other homebrewers involved in advance, or they can write or call me and have their name placed on the &quot;guest list&quot;. Either way, 100 people and the doors close, so move quickly! Really, a celebration of beer and bikes, all for a good cause? What more incentive do you need?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;And bring a scrumptious vegan/vegetarian dish of food with you! (If you contact me about a ticket, let me know if you are planning on making something, so we don&#039;t end up with 100 varieties of lentil soup.)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cheers,&lt;br /&gt;Scott @ Ca-saloon-a&lt;br /&gt;(206) 729.2307 ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[4X', ''),
