(351, 2454485, 2454485, '09:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Seattle&#039;s Really Really Free Market!!! ', '&lt;strong&gt;Really Free Market&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Saturday January 19th&lt;br /&gt;9am to 2pm  &lt;br /&gt;@ the C.A.Y.A. (23rd and Yesler in the Central district)   &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;Really, Really Free Market&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;RRFM&lt;/strong&gt;) movement is a non-&lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hierarchy&quot;&gt;hierarchical&lt;/a&gt; collective of individuals who form a temporary &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Market&quot;&gt;market&lt;/a&gt; based on an alternative &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gift_economy&quot;&gt;gift economy&lt;/a&gt;. The RRFM movement aims to counteract &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capitalism&quot;&gt;capitalism&lt;/a&gt; in a non-reactionary way. It holds as a major goal to build a &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Community&quot;&gt;community&lt;/a&gt; based on sharing resources, caring for one another and improving the collective lives of all. Markets often vary in character, but they generally offer both &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Good_%28economics_and_accounting%29&quot;&gt;goods&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Service_%28economics%29&quot;&gt;services&lt;/a&gt;. Participants bring unneeded items, food, skills and talents such as entertainment or haircuts. A RRFM may take place in an open community space such as a public park or community commons. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
