(429, 2454512, 2454512, '17:30:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'STRAY poetry reading ', 'Stray, a new poetry collective in Seattle, will have its first reading of poems that have been made into art projects by generous art students.  It is free and open to everybody.&lt;br /&gt;What: Poetry reading / Art show&lt;br /&gt;Where: Parnassus Cafe, in the basement of the art building on the UW campus&lt;br /&gt;When: Friday February 15th, 5:30 pm&lt;br /&gt;Why: Because Seattle deserves more poetry, and poetry deserves more parties.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;From the mission statement of Stray:&lt;br /&gt;&quot;Stray is a collective of people who want to revolutionize the state of poetry in the world today, where the practice and celebration of poetry has become stale and limited only to people in academics (who pay lots of money to write about poetry) or published poets (who get paid lots of money to write poetry). There is no such thing as a professional poet. Our poems cannot be bought and sold. There is no form of capital or elitism that can be applied to human expression. Stray seeks to bring the power of composing back to the common people through a variety of methods. Load your poetry guns and lob your poetry grenades. Stray is the new word revolution.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hope to see you there! ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(430, 2454510, 2454510, '12:01:00', '13:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Protest against Primate Torture ', 'Protest against Primate Torture&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;When: Wednesday, Feb 13th @ noon - 1pm&lt;br /&gt;Where: Japanese Consulate (6th and Union)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;PETA has put together a protest to call attention to the horrible cruelty going&lt;br /&gt;on at the SBLA Animal Testing facility in Everett.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you haven&#039;t heard what has been going on at this facility, please check out:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kirotv.com/news/15189249/detail.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.kirotv.com/news/15189249/detail.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.kirotv.com/investigations/15216083/detail.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.kirotv.com/investigations/15216083/detail.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.heraldnet.com/article/20080201/BIZ/963536411/1005&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.heraldnet.com/article/20080201/BIZ/963536411/1005&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://tinyurl.com/2b5b3b&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://tinyurl.com/2b5b3b&lt;/a&gt; (Seattle Times) and&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.all-creatures.org/saen/wa/res-fr-wa-snble.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.all-creatures.org/saen/wa/res-fr-wa-snble.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Signs will be provided, all we need is you. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
(431, 2454511, 2454511, '19:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'I &lt;3 Noise - a Valentines Day Circuit Bending Workshop! ', '@ &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.msplinks.com/MDFodHRwOi8vcHJvZmlsZS5teXNwYWNlLmNvbS9pbmRleC5jZm0/ZnVzZWFjdGlvbj11c2VyLnZpZXdwcm9maWxlJmZyaWVuZGlkPTE2MjE0OTI4OCZNeVRva2VuPWI3ZTJlNThjLTI5YzUtNDRkZC1iYjdmLTk2ODUxNWZlMTBlZg&quot;&gt;THE ARK&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hey babes!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;THE ARK is hosting &quot;I &lt;3 Noise,&quot; a VDAY Circuit Bending Workshop. Kyle, Landon and Jake are going to be helping us bend our toys and make beautiful noises to make our hearts gush and thump. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come over the 14th at 7 PM sharp.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&quot;Here&#039;s what people NEED to bring:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- a set of uninsulated jeweler&#039;s screwdrivers&lt;br /&gt;- a low heat soldering iron and low heat rosin core solder&lt;br /&gt;- ultra mega super fine point sharpie permanent marker(s)&lt;br /&gt;- speaker wrapping wire or other itsy bitsy connecting wire&lt;br /&gt;- needle nose pliers&lt;br /&gt;- wire cutters&lt;br /&gt;- low heat glue gun&lt;br /&gt;- large screws or bolts to use as body contacts&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;also, if people have drills, they should bring them (dremel or otherwise) [We have a drill!]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;voltage meters are optional; i&#039;ve used them a few times, but not that often.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;here&#039;s what people should look for as far as circuit bending targets:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;MOST EXCELLENT:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- any sampling keyboard, such as a casio sk-1, concertmate, rapmaster, etc.&lt;br /&gt;- any of the early eighties learning computers, such as the SPEAK N ____ series, TALKING TEACHER, TOUCH N ____, etc.&lt;br /&gt;- toys with multiple animal sounds!&lt;br /&gt;- basically, any toy that you already think has great sounds before you open it up.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;OK:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- furbies. these are hard to open, easy to fry, but very rewarding.&lt;br /&gt;- late eighties learning computers, such as the SUPER SPEAK N ____ series. you can get good bends out of these, but they crash easily.&lt;br /&gt;- most generic keyboards. you can get goods bends out of them, but usually not very many, and they are prone to crashing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;BAD:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- ANYTHING THAT /MUST/ PLUG INTO THE WALL. NEVER EVER.&lt;br /&gt;- analog keyboards and drum machines. these are great if you really know what you are doing, but random bending will pop tubes, overload circuits, and destroy them.&lt;br /&gt;- anything that will make you cry uncontrollably if it dies on the operating table.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;switches, potentiometers and headphone adapters will be provided.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;i think that&#039;s everything.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;See you then!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hugs,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;THE ARK babes ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
