(526, 2454558, 2454558, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Oliver Herring - Task participant application deadline ', '&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14pt;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;The Frye Art Museum is recruiting 35 participants for &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, a dynamic performance by New York-based artist Oliver Herring and organized by the Frye, The Seattle Public Library, On the Boards, and the Tacoma Art Museum. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14pt;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14pt;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;The performance takes place at The Seattle Public Library Central Library on Saturday, June 28 from 10 am to 5:30 pm.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;What is &lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt;?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;This day-long improvisational performance&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;brings together a group of participants of diverse ages, professions, and backgrounds to create a unique artwork. The performance begins with Herring providing written tasks for participants, who then perform those tasks on stage using an array of simple props. After these initial artist-assigned actions are completed, participants invent and write down their own tasks, placing them in a &amp;ldquo;task pool&amp;rdquo; to be selected and performed by fellow participants on stage. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Inherent to the performance is its unpredictability: the artwork is created by the ideas of those on stage, as well as the relationships formed with one another. Therefore, the nature of the tasks depends on the decisions of the participants, and how they use the props. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;This is the fifth performance of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;by Herring, who most recently created the work for the Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden in Washington, DC (2006). This is the first time &lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt; will be performed in a public building during normal operating hours.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;Task&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt; Partners&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;Frye&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt; Art Museum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.fryemuseum.org/&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#800080&quot;&gt;www.fryemuseum.org&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;The Seattle Public Library: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.spl.org/&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;www.spl.org&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;On the Boards: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ontheboards.org/&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;www.ontheboards.org&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;Tacoma&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt; Art Museum&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.tacomaartmuseum.org/&quot;&gt;www.tacomaartmuseum.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Interested in performing in &lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt;?  What is required? &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;*Interest in creating, interpreting, and executing tasks over the course of a day.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;*Interest in exchanging creative ideas and developing a sense of community through the arts.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;*Willingness to work with a group of 35 people with an audience observing and photographers documenting the process.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;*Availability from 9 am to 7 pm on Saturday, June 28. A brief orientation session with the artist precedes the performance. The performance will last 8 hours total, with two breaks. Food and beverages will be provided throughout the day. Participants are also invited to attend a reception after the performance and discuss their experience with the &lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt; audience. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;*Must be 14 years of age or older.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Volunteering at the &lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt; performance&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Opportunities for individuals interested in volunteering (NOT performing) during &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;will be posted on the partner websites in May and June.  Please check back and join us for the performance!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;How to apply&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Applications are available on the Frye Art Museum website. The deadline for applications is April 1.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Please visit &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.fryemuseum.org/&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#800080&quot; size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;www.fryemuseum.org&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; for a &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Task&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; application.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
