(534, 2454541, 2454541, '09:30:00', '12:01:00', 'Once', 0, 'L. Ron Hubbard&#039;s Birthday Protest! ', '&lt;strong&gt;Operation: Party Hard:&lt;/strong&gt; Join us in &amp;ldquo;celebrating&amp;rdquo; the birthday of L. Ron Hubbard, science fiction writer and creator of the Church of Scientology! There are three locations involved:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Informing The Public about the corruption of The Church of Scientology:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Where: Seattle Center broad street side near the Space Needle.&lt;br /&gt;When: SC Start time: 9:30am Ending around 12:00 noon.&lt;br /&gt;What: Our main target is the Church&amp;rsquo;s tax exemption status. Bring lots of handouts for the public.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Marching Through The Streets&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Where: Westlake Center&lt;br /&gt;When: Gather between 10:00-10:30am, begin walk around 10:30am and arrive at the church around 11:00am.&lt;br /&gt;What: Informing the public at Westlake before taking the message to the streets. Lots of flyers and signs are needed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Main protest&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Where: Church of Scientology Washington 601 Aurora Ave N Seattle, WA 98109&lt;br /&gt;When: Between 11am and Noon all groups will be walking from SC or Westlake to the church on Aurora.&lt;br /&gt;What: Human rights abuses of the church. We need more signs then handouts here as there is very little foot traffic. Lets try to have some civil conversations with the scientologists this time. Again, CIVIL conversations, we want to help, not hurt or degrade them.&lt;br /&gt;End time: When the last person leaves with a scilon tail.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Do not feel you need to do everything, if you want to wait to show up to the main protest, feel free. If you want to head to the church earlier, feel free. Pick what fits best for you, SC with a short walk to church or a little bit more of a walk from Westlake. Lets try to hit our peek numbers at noon at the church.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Recommendations: Bring water, some snacks and wear comfortable shoes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;What we need: Flyer the city with the details. Handouts, lots of handouts. Signs, lots of signs. Anon is serious business but also a little silly so some rickrolling or other fun stuff is needed. Lets find ways to make the public curious about what we are doing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Important: WEAR MASKS TO PROTECT YOUR IDENTITY, IT&#039;S LEGAL.&lt;br /&gt;Do not park near any of the protest locations, do not give your real name to other anons and when you leave BE SURE YOU ARE NOT FOLLOWED. Obey the law at all times, this is a peaceful protest. Stick to the sidewalks unless the permit is approved. If anyone claims to be a leader or acts stupid call them out immediately. If anyone does anything illegal tell the police. Everyone did a great job on 2.10 but 3.15 has the potential to be much larger, so keep your guard up and stay smart. Bring cameras and video cameras.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To get involved, visit: &lt;br /&gt;http://www.lulzinseattle.com/viewforum.php?f=4&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more info about Anonymous and the Church of Scientology, visit:&lt;br /&gt;http://www.religionisfree.org/wiki/index.php/Main_Page ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
(536, 2454551, 2454551, '19:30:00', '23:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'Gravy Train!!!!, New Bloods and joey casio @ The Vera Project ', 'March 25 - 7:30 PM&lt;br /&gt;Gravy Train!!!!&lt;br /&gt;New Bloods (PDX)&lt;br /&gt;Joey Casio&lt;br /&gt;$8 ($7 w/ club card)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Gravy Train!!!!, Oakland&#039;s finest electropop outfit is coming through Seattle to The Vera Project on Tuesday March 25 - 7:30 PM and a party is sure to follow. Yes, Chunx, Hunx, Funx, and Junx are bringing all their sweet stuff to Vera and we couldn&#039;t be more excited! On top of that we have some amazing openers to boot. New Bloods, are Portland&#039;s finest all-girl violin toting, Kill Rock Stars signed punk group ever, and everyone who missed them at Wild Rose last year should definitely come and see New Bloods now. Opener Joey Casio is an unbelievable Olympia electro-punk one man dance band. He is an exciting performer who never ever disappoints. See Gravy Train!!!! this time they come through. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
