(551, 2454556, 2454556, '19:00:00', '21:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Intellectual Property Is Intellectual Theft Film Night ', 'This SUNDAY come watch an extra-special collection of short documentaries about&lt;br /&gt; Open Source ethics in computing, culture and politics!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Including such remarkable short documentaries as:&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; -The History of Hacking&lt;br /&gt; -The World&#039;s Most Important 6 Second Drum Loop&lt;br /&gt; -Rise of the Cyber Pirates!&lt;br /&gt; -This Awesome Recording Industry Association of America Training Video for Cops&lt;br /&gt; About How Busting Pirates Will Win the Wars on Drugs and Terror at the Same&lt;br /&gt; Time!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; You choose our Final Film!!  Either we watch:&lt;br /&gt; -An inspiring lecture by Richard Stallman, Founder of the Free Software&lt;br /&gt; Foundation and author of the GPL ((the software licence that defines Open&lt;br /&gt; Source and Free Software))&lt;br /&gt; OR&lt;br /&gt; -An inspiring lecture by Lawrence Lessig, founder of the Free Culture movement&lt;br /&gt; and author of the Creative Commons Licence ((like the GPL for art))&lt;br /&gt; OR&lt;br /&gt; -Superstar, the film that dares to tell the tragic story of the death of Karen&lt;br /&gt; Carpenter using Barbie Dolls instead of actors, withdrawn from circulation in&lt;br /&gt; 1990 after the director lost a copyright infringement lawsuit filed by Richard&lt;br /&gt; Carpenter.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Come and get nerdy with your radical self with your friends at the Monsterssori&lt;br /&gt; Microcinema.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; What:  7 PM - Intellectual Property Is Intellectual Theft Films&lt;br /&gt; When:  Sunday, March 30th, 7-9 PM&lt;br /&gt; Where:  Monsterssori House, 2317 14th Ave S,, Beacon Hill&lt;br /&gt; Cost: $0.00&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Monsterssori Microcinema is a great new experience for your minds and hearts&lt;br /&gt; and brains.  Two Sundays a month there will be free screeni