(589, 2454562, 2454562, '12:01:00', '16:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Linux skillshare and install-fest ', 'We can work together to install linux on computers which people have brought, and chat about what free software means, why using proprietary software is supporting the man, why radical projects should use free software, sexism in technology, and whatever else. For people who aren&#039;t ready to switch over to linux, we can chat about and/or install free-software programs (like firefox &amp; open office). And for people who don&#039;t have computers or are afraid of them, we can still sit around &amp; chat about all this.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Geeky boys who are being too geeky-boy-ish might be asked to help prepare snacks or do the dishes...&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Also, we&#039;ll be working together, and nobody will be an expert. Installing linux on a PC desktop or not-brand-new laptop should be relatively straight-forward, but if anybody has a Mac or some other configuration (Xbox, cell phone, random electronics found in the trash, etc..), be warned that it might be more of a challenge. But challenges can be fun...&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Location: 1309 13th Avenue South&lt;br /&gt;For information email diylinuxworkshop@riseup.net ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
