(624, 2454684, 2454685, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'BOUND FOR GLORY - based on the life of Woody Guthrie ', 'AUGUST 5 - 6, Tuesday - Wednesday at 7, 9:30pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BOUND FOR GLORY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(Hal Ashby, USA, 1976, 35mm, 145 min) &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Based on the life of Woody Guthrie, BOUND FOR GLORY explores the social, economic and political hardships that molded the legendary folk singer&amp;rsquo;s beliefs. Beginning with his life in Texas and his terrible experiences in the Southwest Dust Bowl, the film follows Guthrie as he moves to California to begin his radio career. There he discovers the political power of music, which he harnesses by writing and singing his own songs. BOUND FOR GLORY broke new ground as the first feature film in which the Steadicam was used. For his brilliant work, director of photography Haskell Wexler took home an Oscar. The film, which was produced by music promoter Harold Leventhal, was also recognized for its score, which was based on Guthrie&#039;s own music.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &quot;Elegantly crafted, hugely beautiful and interesting film, which reveals loving integrity in every frame.&quot; -LOS ANGELES TIMES&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;NORTHWEST FILM FORUM&lt;br /&gt;Tickets at www.nwfilmforum.org ', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(625, 2454652, 2454658, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'THE GITS ', '&lt;br /&gt;JULY 4 - 10, Friday- Thursday at 7, 9pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE GITS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(Kerri O&#039;Kane, 2007, Digi-BETA, 80 min)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In a pre-Nirvana Seattle, The Gits were the resident musical underdogs. With the unparalleled vocal power of front woman Mia Zapata they set the bar for indie rock in the Pacific Northwest. After inspiring such incendiary bands as Seven Year Bitch to pick up their instruments, they caught the ear of major label record execs who heard the muscular riffs and soulful hooks and realized what fans already knew &amp;ndash; The Gits were anything but your typical street punk outfit. Because of this, the tragedy that struck in 1993 was that much harder to swallow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With intimate live footage and interviews with the surviving members, director Kerri O&amp;rsquo;Kane explores the mystique and digs into the mystery of one of the rock world&amp;rsquo;s most enigmatic bands. One part The Filth and The Fury, one part CSI: Seattle, THE GITS is a rock doc as engaging and powerful as the music that inspired it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;NORTHWEST FILM FORUM - www.nwfilmforum.org ', 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(626, 2454655, 2454655, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'PROFIT MOTIVE AND THE WHISPERING WIND ', '&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;PROFIT MOTIVE AND THE WHISPERING WIND&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(John Gianvito, USA, 2007, Digi-BETA, 58 min)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A calm, beautiful and wordless testament to fallen rebels and radicals in American history, from colonial times to the present. The film consists of elegantly composed images of gravesites and public shrines. A monument to monuments and a call to arms, PROFIT MOTIVE visits the resting places of such figures as Malcolm X, Mother Jones, Cesar Chavez and Eugene V. Debs. Winner, Best Experimental Film, 2007, National Society Film Critics.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Screen with&lt;br /&gt;PERFECT FILM&lt;br /&gt;(Ken Jacobs, USA, 1986, 16mm, 22 min)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An experimental work structured around outtakes from TV news footage after the assassination of Malcolm X.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;JULY 7 at 8pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;NORTHWEST FILM FORUM - www.nwfilmforum.org ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(627, 2454660, 2454660, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'THE KIDS OF WIDNEY HIGH ', '&lt;br /&gt;JULY 12, Saturday at 7pm&lt;br /&gt;LIVE PERFORMANCE!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE KIDS OF WIDNEY HIGH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The world-renowned Kids of Widney High are a group of young adults with developmental disabilities who write, record and perform their own unique brand of rock music.  They have been compared to Daniel Johnston and Wesley Willis. For the first time in their illustrious underground career, the Kids are embarking on a full-fledged multimedia tour up the West Coast in which they will be showcasing their artistic endeavors, which include short films that evoke the &quot;gaze&quot; avant-garde aesthetic of Stan Brakhage, Harry Smith and Jonas Mekas. The Kids will be performing after the screening for all audience members who wish to stay and boogie.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;NORTHWEST FILM FORUM - www.nwfilmforum.org ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(628, 2454668, 2454668, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'SEATTLE BIKE IN! ', '&lt;br /&gt;JULY 20, Sunday starting at 4pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;SEATTLE BIKE-IN&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At Cal Anderson Park&lt;br /&gt;Northwest Film forum teams up with Sustainable Capitol Hill to bring you this year&#039;s Seattle&#039;s Bike-In. Entering its third year of supporting alternative transportation in the city, this year&#039;s partnership includes an all day event called Imagine Capitol Hill, where Sustainable Capitol Hill and its partners provide information and entertainment about sustainable issues facing Capitol Hill residents. Imagine Capitol Hill takes place at the Broadway Farmers market and is followed by a bicycle parade to Cal Anderson Park for music and movies!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Presented by Northwest Film Forum - FREE! ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(629, 2454701, 2454701, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'SUMMER OF &#039;68 REVISITED ', 'AUGUST 22 - 24&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;SUMMER OF &#039;68 REVISITED&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A Texan was in office; the US was entrenched in war; there was a hotly contested Democratic presidential campaign in which both candidates opposed the war, sought social reforms, and sought improvement in civil rights in America. Inside a convention building, delegates voted for their presidential candidate, but they did not choose the candidate who had done well in the early primary elections. Instead they chose the more traditional candidate. Sound familiar? This short series, slated just days before this years&amp;rsquo; Democratic Convention, delivers a films from 1968, and a return to an era both similar and dissimilar to our own. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;AUGUST 22 - 24, Friday - Sunday at 7, 9:15pm &lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MEDIUM COOL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(Haskell Wexler, USA, 1969, 35mm, 110 min)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Talk about WILD IN THE STREETS! Oscar-winning cinematographer Haskell Wexler (WHO&amp;rsquo;S AFRAID OF VIRGINIA WOOLF?, BOUND FOR GLORY) produced, directed, wrote and shot this very cool, very radical end-of-the-60s artifact, a cinéma vérité-style drama set against &amp;mdash; and actually filmed during &amp;mdash; the infamous 1968 Democratic Convention in Chicago, where hippies, Yippies and other anti-Vietnam War protestors engaged police in bloody battle on the city streets. Robert Forster (JACKIE BROWN, MULHOLLAND DRIVE) plays a detached TV news cameraman who becomes conscious of the political and ethical ramifications of his work when the FBI begins using his footage to identity militants. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;One of the most devastating and technically sophisticated anti-establishment films ever made. Taking its title almost straight from mouth of media guru Marshall McLuhan&amp;hellip;[MEDIUM COOL] film remains a landmark of political cinema and an insightful essay on the &amp;lsquo;cool medium.&#039;&amp;rdquo; -James Monaco, THE ENCYCLOPEDIA OF FILM&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;AUGUST 23 - 24, Saturday - Sunday at 3, 5pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMER &#039;68&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;(Norman Fruchter and John Douglas, 1969, BETA, 60 min)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Fruchter and Douglas craft a compelling document of the events leading up to the volatile 1968 Democratic National Convention in Chicago. Focusing specifically on the growth of the radical movement in the U.S., the film presents the struggle for students and activists to find a proper medium for their message.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Screens with&lt;br /&gt;CHICAGO CONVENTION CHALLENGE&lt;br /&gt;(Newsreel Collective,  USA, 1968, 17 min)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Using newsreel footage taken in the midst of demonstrations against the Vietnam War during the 1968 Democratic National Convention, this film conveys the immediacy of anti-war organizing in meeting rooms, at rallies and in the streets. It is a valuable historical portrait of events that culminated in police riots against the protesters. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(630, 2454589, 2454589, '12:01:00', '16:20:00', 'Once', 0, 'MARIJUANA LIBERATION MARCH, Volunteer Park @ Noon Saturday ', '&lt;em&gt;Are you hella tired of the feds taking away your rights?&lt;br /&gt;Is hemp useful, and should we cuitivate much more of it?&lt;br /&gt;D&#039;you share the prevailing opinion that hempfest kicks ass?&lt;br /&gt;Do you love to smoke/vaporize/cook with reefer?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VOLUNTEER PARK, NOON, SATURDAY. It&#039;ll be at Westlake later. The website&#039;s &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://worldwidemarijuanamarch.org/&quot;&gt;http://worldwidemarijuanamarch.org&lt;/a&gt;. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
(645, 2454610, 2454610, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Alas, alak, Alaska!, Wooden Indian Burial Ground, Afternoon Borther and Brad Dunn at the Office of Dr. Glorious! ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Hello all,&lt;br /&gt;So, next Friday we have are having a show, that we are very excited to be hosting. Hopefully, you can come and check it out because you really don&#039;t want to miss this one!..&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Friday May 23rd at the Office of Dr. Glorious..&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Alas, alak, Alaska! from California (www. myspace. com/alasalakalaska) For those of you who have not really seen her play, Jocelyn plays strangely beautiful folk songs with awesome lyrics. Perhaps, they are the lost transmissions of folkies from other solar systems or Appalacian sounds from a parallel universe?..&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Wooden Indian Burial Ground are from Portland. (www. myspace. com/woodenindianburialground) Wooden Indian Burial Ground are a two piece. They use banjo, percussion, harmonica and vocals and swirl it all together into a druken stew of broken hearts and lost ways.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Afternoon Brother who apparentally is from Burger City, California. (www. myspace. com/afternoonbrother) Crazy, techy, madness that I have no idea how to describe. Really weird and disorienting, but who doesn&#039;t like being disoriented from time to time? This band will fuck with your head!..&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Brad Dunn who is from the great city of Seattle. Ever been there? (www. myspace. com/modocos) One time, we picked up Brad Dunn on a street corner. He was hitch hiking to win a race against some friends of his that were on bikes. We got to where he was going just as his friends were locking their bikes. He sprung from the car and won via suprise attack! So, Bradd Dunn is the kind of guy who wins races via suprise attack, oh yeah, and he also plays music! How can you doubt someone&#039;s music, when they win via suprise attack? Expect to be attacked and suprised!..&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;So, you really don&#039;t want to miss this one, do you? On a serious note, please bring money for the touring bands and buy their cd&#039;s or records. Gas prices are very close to $4 a gallon, which is an insane amount of money for a band on the road to have to pay. This price increase poses a serious threat to the future of our music scene. please support touring musicians, so we don&#039;t lose the d.i.y. infrastructure that we have all spent years creating.  It&#039;s more important now than ever!&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
