(809, 2454694, 2454694, '14:00:00', '16:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Zinery Class at the Columbia Branch Library ', 'Lots of random things to cut up, stencils, stamps, scissors, glue sticks, and snacks... It&#039;s a very basic zine-making class. We do a short bit of introduction and then folks make a four page zine with a cover. So if this is your magical world, you should come out. Three cheers for public libraries!&lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;  Please bring materials with you if you have a specific project in mind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Columbia Branch&lt;br /&gt; -preregistration at the branch requested&lt;br /&gt; Hosted by Lucy M. (Ong Ong Fanzine)&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; p.s. If you&#039;re feeling more advanced than this, please feel free to come for the supplies, to ask complicated questions, or to inspire newcomers. Long live print media! ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
