(961, 2454694, 2454694, '20:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Cabinet of Natural Curiosities + The Precambrian @ Gallery 1412 ', '&lt;p&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Cabinet of Natural Curiosities&lt;br /&gt;The Precambrian&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Friday, August 15th&lt;br /&gt;Gallery 1412  &lt;br /&gt; (1412 18th Ave - Seattle, WA)&lt;br /&gt; 8:00 PM sharp&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; CABINET OF NATURAL CURIOSITIES&lt;br /&gt;Cabinet of Natural Curiosities is an experimental folk collective from Missoula, Montana, and Brooklyn, NY. Led by vocalist/guitarist/sound artist Jasmine Dreame Wagner, Cabinet of Natural Curiosities performs experimental folk chants and noise instrumentals, ghost stories and historical ballads over field recordings, acoustic &amp; classical guitars, electric effects, alto &amp; tenor recorders, bells and percussion.&lt;/p&gt;     &lt;p&gt;THE PRECAMBRIAN&lt;br /&gt; The Precambrian is a constantly evolving interactive synthesis environment/instrument, engineered &amp; performed by Ben L. Robertson (using the graphical programming language, Max/MSP).  This performance apparatus is accompanied by vocalist/sound designer, Andrew Senna, who executes drones &amp; synthetic onomatopoeia, indicative of his &lt;span style=&quot;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;background-attachment:scroll;&quot;&gt;sound design work&lt;/span&gt; for film &amp; theater.  In its current incarnation, The Precambrian utilizes a &quot;slide zither&quot;, analog synthesizer, voice, &amp; various pitch recognition algorithms to coax out microtonal intervals derived from a graphical system of 11-limit, just intonation matrices. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://aphoniarecordings.com&quot;&gt;www.aphoniarecordings.com&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
