(982, 2454709, 2454709, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Community Film Night (near Judkins park) ', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Community Film Night&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When:  &lt;/strong&gt;Saturday August 30th at 8pm&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Where:&lt;/strong&gt; 730 24th Ave S (between Dearborne and Lane)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;Screening in the back yard (inside if rain)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;Come celebrate grassroots communities and independent media with your family, neighbors and pets in the backyard screening of &amp;ldquo;Boom: The Sound of Eviction&amp;rdquo;.  &amp;ldquo;Boom&amp;rdquo; is an inspiring and heartfelt film that depicts the gentrification of San Francisco&amp;rsquo;s Mission District and the bottom-up resistance to the displacement of communities. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Snacks, coffee and hot chocolate will be provided.  Please bring blankets and try to get there early, chairs may be scarce.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sponsor&lt;/strong&gt;: 	The &lt;em&gt;Participator&lt;/em&gt;: a collective newspaper written and edited by students at Seattle U. &lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;	theparticipator@gmail.com	&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt