(1139, 2454750, 2454750, '19:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Film: *Christiania: Our Heart is in Your Hands*  ', 'Bus No. 8 presents a work-in-progress screening of&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Christiania: Our Heart is in Your Hands*&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*Friday, October 10th, 7:00pm*&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*Nordic Heritage Museum *- 3014 NW 67th Street, Seattle, WA&lt;br /&gt;$5.00 suggested donation, available at the door&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*Christiania: Our Heart is in Your Hands* chronicles a 37-year-old anarchist squatter community occupying an abandoned military base in Copenhagen, Denmark.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;After years of building a unique culture based on group consensus, cottage industries and a famous, though problematic, hash trade - Christiania&#039;s existence is threatened.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;But what might ultimately be its downfall - government bureaucrats trying to &quot;normalize&quot; Christiania?  Developers hungry for its valuable real estate?  Or the decline of youthful energy that forged this cultural frontier?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The screening will be followed by a panel discussion with filmmakers Richard Jackman and Robert Lawson, and Marianne Stecher-Hansen, UW Associate Professor of Danish Studies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;More information at the Nordic Heritage Museum &lt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.nordicmuseum.org/index.php?t&quot;&gt;http://www.nordicmuseum.org/index.php?t=events&amp;c=full&amp;e=413&lt;/a&gt;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;See clips from the film &lt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://busno8.com/CA.html&quot;&gt;http://busno8.com/CA.html&lt;/a&gt;&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
