(1157, 2454765, 2454765, '20:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'land what land, dbh, steve arntson, squirrelhead at Gallery 1412 ', 'land what land:&lt;br /&gt;a celebration and reconciling of the places we carry in our bodies; of the things we have seen, felt, eaten and heard. strings and deserts, drums and fire, forests and voices, blood everywhere.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;myspace.com/omiimii&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;dbh:&lt;br /&gt;Experimental soundscapes from seething midwestern cornfields, darkly colored orchestration and rural poetics, moldy electronics, scraping metal, and 2 ghostly voices pulling it all together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;steve arntson:&lt;br /&gt;Steven R. Arntson is a Seattle-based composer of music for the 30-button Anglo concertina, who has performs locally in a variety of dank, crowded cellars.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;stevenarntson.info&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;squirrelhead:&lt;br /&gt;love songs for best friends, optimists and the reincarnated. ukulele, strings and words, yes, and humming. oh! and birds.....&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;myspace.com/squirrelheadlove&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;gallery 1412&lt;br /&gt;1412 18th ave (18th and union)&lt;br /&gt;$5-15 sliding scale / pay what you can&lt;br /&gt;www.gallery1412.org ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(1158, 2454772, 2454772, '20:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Diane Cluck, KnotPineBox, Malcolm Rollick at Gallery 1412 ', 'Diane Cluck is loosely affiliated with the Anti-folk scene centered around open mic nights at the Sidewalk Cafe in Manhattan&#039;s East Village in NYC. She moved to Stone Mountain, Georgia in January 2007.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&quot;Dogs inspire me and break my heart. They are joyfull by nature and honest at all times. People imprison and domesticate dogs, rob them of their sex organs and then keep them around to stroke on. Humans keep pets as models of their own restraint. I am interested in &#039;freeing the dog&#039;.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;myspace.com/dianecluck&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;KnotPineBox, AKA Karen Hancock, has been playing guitar a while. Originally working with songwriting in bands like Flicker, Violet Ray and PineBox, her music has progressed into found sound collage. KnotPineBox is a solo melodic improv project using simple sound effects with guitar, tapes and toys. All samples are live and imagery is sometimes recycled. She also records and performs with the Seattle electro/folk/downtempo band Saba.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;knotpinebox.com&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;note: &lt;/strong&gt;Malcolm Rollick will not be performing at this show, as previously announced.  we thought she was, but she&#039;s not.  sorry about that.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;gallery 1412&lt;br /&gt;1412 18th ave (18th and union)&lt;br /&gt;$5-15 sliding scale&lt;br /&gt;www.gallery1412.org ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
