(1220, 2454779, 2454779, '12:01:00', '14:00:00', 'Once', 0, '@ The Bikery ', '&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Winter Bike Crafts!!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As winter approaches, this community forum will give us a chance to share bike craft ideas to keep us occupied during the indoor months.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Want to learn how to knit a bike cozie? Want to find patterns for bike helmet-ear warmers? Want to learn how to turn all of those political signs into fenders? (Now that the election&#039;s over, you can bring along political signs to recycle with this project.)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bring along patterns that you&#039;ve found, and we&#039;ll have some to share too!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Bikery:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;1265 S Main St. #104 Seattle (In the Central District)&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1221, 2454786, 2454786, '14:00:00', '17:00:00', 'Once', 0, '@ The Bikery ', '&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Bikery&#039;s GRAND OPENING Celebration! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will be holding an open house for the community to get to know the Bikery. Come check out our new space and services! We will also need volunteers who can serve as &quot;greeters&quot; for the people coming to check us out. Please email volunteer@thebikery.org for more information about how you can help or call(206) 568-3535.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Bikery:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;1265 S Main St. #104 Seattle (In the Central District)&lt;br /&gt;    ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[2X', ''),
(1222, 2454787, 2454787, '12:01:00', '14:00:00', 'Once', 0, '@ The Bikery ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Know Your Rights!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;    * Is it illegal to ride a bike in the middle of a lane of traffic?&lt;br /&gt;    * Are you supposed to signal for turns with your left or right hand?&lt;br /&gt;    * What about using a crosswalk to avoid swerving through six lanes of traffic?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;These and other topics are included in our conversation-based Know Your Rights workshop, designed to allow cyclists an opportunity to share experiences, survival skills, long-unanswered questions, and much more.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This &quot;Know Your Rights&quot; class will be followed by a community ride. If you can&#039;t make it to the class, you can meet up at the Bikery at 2pm.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Bikery:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;1265 S Main St. #104 Seattle (In the Central District)&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;  ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[2X', ''),
(1223, 2454781, 2454781, '17:30:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Transform Yourself: An Introduction to Stages of Ego Development ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seattle Free School&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Transform Yourself: An Introduction to Stages of Ego Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Greater clarity, wisdom, empowerment, fulfillment, sense of belonging and purpose - we all want that. In this class, we&#039;re bringing the works of pioneers in the field of human potential and development into mainstream awareness by introducing a theory of the stages of adult ego development. You&#039;ll learn about the 10 stages, how to recognize which stage you tend to operate from, and how you might continue to develop yourself.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Facilitators- Lain Kahlstrom- Integral coach and student of human development and Wendy Visconty- CPA, coach and student of human development&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Go to website to register: http://seattlefreeschool.googlepages.com/classes ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1224, 2454779, 2454779, '13:00:00', '15:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Mead Making 101 ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seattle Free School&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mead Making 101&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come learn how to make mead and other fruit wines! This class covers what you need, as well as basic recipes (including non-alcoholic mead for the little ones), and a brief history of mead.&lt;br /&gt;Please note: there will be no actual brewing or tasting of alcohol during this class. All ages welcome.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Facilitator &amp;ndash; Beth Wade&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Go to website to sign-up: http://seattlefreeschool.googlepages.com/classes ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1225, 2454779, 2454779, '13:00:00', '15:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Knitting and Crochet with Plastic ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seattle Free School&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Knitting and Crochet with Plastic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Take your plastic bags-grocery bags, bread bags, newspaper bags and turn them into a usable durable fiber.  Students should have a basic understanding of knitting and/or crochet or a willingness to experiment.  In addition students will get an overview of tote-bag, hat, and/or rug creation and pattern design.  These make great frugal Christmas gifts!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Supplies students must bring:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;**Clean plastic bags (do not use the plastic bags used for meats for health reasons.), tape measure, scissors, J crochet hook/size 11 knitting needles or a comfortable size of either, pencil and notebook.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Facilitator- Clare Cronkleton&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Go to website to sign-up: http://seattlefreeschool.googlepages.com/classes&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;                       ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
