(1289, 2454849, 2454849, '10:00:00', '14:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Primitive Skills and Permaculture, meet-up and Skillshare ', 'This is a free event at Seward Park on Saturday, January 17th, from 10am-2pm. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;What would can you share?&lt;br /&gt;What would you like to learn?&lt;br /&gt;Bring materials, kids, snacks for lunch, and interest. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This event is hosted by the Seattle Permaculture Guild. &lt;br /&gt;Post your project either on &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.permies.com/permaculture-forums/1071_0/events/primitive-skills-and-permaculture-skillshare&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;permies.com&lt;/a&gt; or at the &lt;a href=&quot;http://seattlepermacultureguild.org/wiki/wiki.php?n&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;seattle permaculture website&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more info, or for someone to post your project for you, contact Kelda. kelda @ riseup . net or 253-370-9946.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#039;Primitive Skills&#039; refers to prehistoric handicrafts and pre-industrial technologies (wilderness survival, ethnobotany)&lt;br /&gt;&#039;Permaculture&#039; is a design system for creating sustainable human habitats (food growing, water harvesting, appropriate technologies). ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1290, 2454838, 2454838, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'anarchist bookfair meeting. ', 'for anyone who is interested, a seattle anarchist bookfair is in the works and we are looking for people who can give their time to planning and setting up the bookfair.  this will be our first meeting and we will be discussing everything from where and when to have the bookfair to fundraising ideas to who to invite, etc.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;we are going to meet 7p this evening on the second level of bauhaus.  anyone interested, please feel free to join us.  bring friends and spread the word. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
(1291, 2454812, 2454812, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Life &amp; Debt Film (for Indymedia at SU) ', '&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Movie Night! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Life &amp; Debt&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;to support independent media at Seattle University&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Life and Debt&lt;/em&gt; examines the economic and social situation in Jamaica, focusing on the legacy of colonialism and global economic policies that have left the country in a dire condition. The film explores the role of the International Monetary Fund and the World Bank in ending many social services and increasing economic dependency. Through out the film the narrator reads from the award-winning non-fiction essay &lt;em&gt;A Small Place&lt;/em&gt; by Jamaica Kincaid, which makes the link between tourism, western culture, globalization, and racism.  We invite you to attend the screening Life and Debt, which shows a powerful, honest and humanizing portrayal of the situation in Jamaica.  &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Come celebrate the end of the year with a movie night! There will be popcorn, coffee and snacks, but please feel free to bring any treats! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*** We will be asking for donations throughout the evening, however no one will be turned away due to lack of funds.  All money will go toward The Participator, an independent-activist newspaper at Seattle University. ***&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Location: 730 24th Ave s (between Dearborne and Lane)&lt;br /&gt;Time: Thursday December 11 at 8pm &lt;br /&gt;Bus: 4 and 48 stop one block away!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Contact: &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;mailto:theparticipator@gmail.com&quot;&gt;theparticipator@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
