(1328, 2454855, 2454855, '19:00:00', '21:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Comixtravaganza: Comic Workshop at the South Park Community Center with Greg Stump ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Attend a hands on drawing a workshop with professional comic artist Greg Stump!  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.trumba.com/i/DgCgbf7WbYbspECRCc3WfaLU.gif&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Greg Stump has been teaching comics and cartooning to students of all ages for more than a decade. Experience comic-making with a pro, plus snacks and dinner!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Library events and programs are free and everyone is welcome. Registration is not required. Dinner will be provided and served at 9 p.m.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more information, call the South Park Branch at 206-615-1688 or &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.spl.org/default.asp?pageID&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Ask a Librarian&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;.&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[6X', ''),
(1329, 2454860, 2454860, '18:30:00', '08:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Comixtravaganza: Comix Workshop with David Lasky and Greg Stump at the Ballard Branch ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Let David Lasky and Greg Stump, the co-creators of Urban Hipster, unlock your inner artist at their Comix Workshop.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Are you inspired by the work of comics illustrators and writers? Are you already working on a project? Are you stuck? Bring a friend and join us at the Ballard Branch for a chance to get some valuable guidance and ideas from David Lasky and Greg Stump, co-creators of the Urban Hipster. Supplies and refreshments provided.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Library events and programs are free and everyone is welcome. Registration is not required.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more information, call the Ballard Branch at 206-684-4089 or &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.spl.org/default.asp?pageID&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Ask a Librarian&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;.&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[6X', ''),
(1404, 2454866, 2454866, '19:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Flim Night at Gallery 1412 ', '&lt;strong&gt;Flim Night: an evening of projectable phenomena&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;This month we celebrate the &lt;strong&gt;one year birthday&lt;/strong&gt; of Flim Night!&lt;br /&gt;hooray!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;featuring:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;The Cyclist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mohsen Makhmalbaf, Iran, 1987, 83 minutes&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makhmalbaf.com/movies.php?m&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;makhmalbaf.com/movies.php?m=22&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;A poor, Afgan immigrant well digger named Nasim (Moharram Zaynalzadeh) distractedly watches on with his son as a friend performs his daredevil motorcycle act. Nasim&#039;s thoughts are consumed by his gravely ill wife, and the hospital&#039;s reluctance to continue to provide treatment without receiving payment for her incurred medical expenses. Unable to raise enough money from his itinerant work, Nasim unsuccessfully attempts to perpetrate several underhanded schemes...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;&quot;[&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;The Cyclist&lt;/span&gt;] confirmed Makhmalbaf&#039;s unique ability to turn a grotesque subject into a rich and fertile film which teases the brain while pulling on the heartstrings&quot; - Deborah Young, International Film Guide&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;&quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;The Cyclist&lt;/span&gt;... is probably the closest we have ever come to seeing a pataphysical film&quot; -  Michael Richardson, Surrealism and Cinema&amp;lrm;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;and, as usual, &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;cartoons&lt;/span&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;On the first Tuesday of every month, &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Flim Night&lt;/span&gt; showcases a variety of film-based art, with special emphasis on subversive humor, surrealism, activist and revolutionary topics, and whatever else resonates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;donations benefit&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt; Seattle Food Not Bombs&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scn.org/foodnotbombs&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;scn.org/foodnotbombs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;gallery 1412&lt;br /&gt;1412 18th ave (18th and union)&lt;br /&gt;gallery1412.org&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;7pm&lt;br /&gt;$5-15 suggested ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(1330, 2454863, 2454863, '12:01:00', '13:15:00', 'Once', 0, 'Comixtravaganza: One-Hour Comix with Davey Oil at the Central Library ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Davey Oil, cartoonist extraordinaire, dares you to try your hand at creating your own comic book--in just one hour!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We&#039;ll provide the pencils, paper, and other art supplies--you provide the creativity. In one hour you&#039;ll have a glorious comic. You can even choose to have your comic photocopied and added to the zine collection at Central Library!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Library events and programs are free and everyone is welcome. Registration is not required.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more information, call the Central Library Teen Center 206-615-1410 or &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;mailto:%20TeenCenter@spl.org&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;E-mail the Teen Center&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;.&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[6X', ''),
