(1400, 2454851, 2454851, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'march with CARW! ', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;URGENT ACTION:&lt;/font&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Calling All White Anti-Racist Allies! &lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Martin Luther King Jr. Rally and March&lt;/font&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Monday January 19th at Garfield High School (23rd &amp; Jefferson) Rally at 11am and March to Downtown at 12pm&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Come and join the Coalition of Anti-Racist Whites (CARW) and community members at Seattle&#039;s 27th Annual MLK march and rally. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;This event is especially important because one of CARW&#039;s ally organizations, El Comité Pro-Reforma Migratoria y Justicia Social, has asked us to march alongside them!  With a mass presence of accountable white allies at the MLK rally and march, we will further strengthen our commitment  to El Comité as well as our commitment to the struggle against racism.  &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Please invite all your friends, co-workers, organizations, classes and families to this historic event!&lt;/font&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Meet up with CARW folks near the &quot;Stop the Raids and Deportations&quot; banner between the gym and auditorium during the rally.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Seattle&#039;s MLK Jr. Day website:&lt;/font&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://owa.seattleu.edu/exchweb/bin/redir.asp?URL&quot;&gt;http://www.mlkseattle.org/index.php&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;CARW website:&lt;/font&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;ht