(1439, 2454874, 2454874, '18:30:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'SHACHAF POLOKOW Speaks in Seattle ', 'SHACHAF POLOKOW Speaks in Seattle&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; When:  Wednesday, February 11, 2009 at 7:15 pm&gt;  (Doors open at 6:30 to&lt;br /&gt; socialize and share snacks and sweets with Schachaf)&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Where:  Friends Center, Social Hall 4001 9th Ave.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Donation $10.00 or what you can afford.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; An Israeli member of Anarchists Against the Wall, Schachaf will talk about&lt;br /&gt; the work of that group and his experiences in solidarity with Palestinians&lt;br /&gt; in Nilin and other villages in the West Bank&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; This is a fundraising event to raise money to support the work of AATW and&lt;br /&gt; to help meet legal costs for both Palestinians and Israelis arrested in&lt;br /&gt; the course of non-violent protests against the Separation wall being built&lt;br /&gt; on Palestinian land. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
(1440, 2454870, 2454870, '20:00:00', '23:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'ACTIVITY, DATE &amp; DESSERT AUCTION—Sat Feb 7 at 8pm ', '&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.meetup.com/Seattle-Veg-Singles/calendar/9520190/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;When:&lt;strong&gt; Saturday Feb 7 at 8:00pm   &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Where:&lt;strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.meetup.com/Seattle-Veg-Singles/venue/442808/?eventId&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0066cc&quot;&gt;Skin Deep Dance Studios&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; at 2524 16th Ave S #311, Seattle   &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; at 2524 16th Ave S #311, Seattle   at 2524 16th Ave S #311, Seattle   &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come auction off a skill, activity, date or vegan dessert to help animals! Or just be the highest bidder and win one of these for yourself! All proceeds benefit &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.narn.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0066cc&quot;&gt;Northwest Animal Rights Network&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. For more information about NARN&amp;rsquo;s animal protection campaigns, please visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.narn.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0066cc&quot;&gt;www.narn.org&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.   &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please email a brief description of the activity, date or vegan dessert you are offering and your starting bid to &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:volunteer@narn.org&quot;&gt;volunteer@narn.org&lt;/a&gt;. Signing up in advance is not required, but it&amp;rsquo;s recommended.   ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(1460, 2454883, 2454883, '19:00:00', '21:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'DUCK FUNERAL PROCESSION: 7pm ', '&lt;a href=&quot;http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/6/5/f/highres_8614399.jpeg&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/6/5/f/global_8614399.jpeg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;    &lt;p&gt;To bring attention to the cruelty to ducks inherent in foie gras production, please join &lt;a href=&quot;/calendar/events/www.narn.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;NARN&#039;s&lt;/a&gt; Duck Funeral Procession on Friday May 15. You&#039;re asked to wear all black that day, dressing as though attending a real funeral. Ladies, feel free to wear a black veil; men, wear a dark suit if you like. Or just wear any black clothes. We&#039;ll have a eulogy, candles, bells, weeping, and frequent silence to create a ceremoniously somber mood.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We will meet at Lark at &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://maps.google.com/maps?f&quot;&gt;926 12th Ave E&lt;/a&gt; on Capitol Hill at 7pm, then process over to Quinn&amp;rsquo;s Pub at &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://maps.google.com/maps?f&quot;&gt;1001 E Pike St&lt;/a&gt; at 8pm.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[7X', ''),
(1442, 2454884, 2454884, '14:00:00', '15:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'Fruit Tree Pruning Workshop @ Emma&#039;s ', 'Wondering what to do with that old fruit tree in your backyard? Scared of that scraggly mess of grape vines? Are your branches breaking from too much fruit? Come join us as we do a winter pruning on the fruit trees at the Emma G House. We will be working on plum, cherry &amp; apple trees, as well as grape vines.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Fruit Tree Pruning Workshop&lt;br /&gt;@ Emma Goldman Finishing School&lt;br /&gt;1309 13th ave sin North Beacon Hill &lt;br /&gt;2pm-3:30pm&lt;br /&gt;Free&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;for more information contact chandler at riseup.net ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1443, 2454864, 2454894, '18:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Floating', 12, 'BoUnce: The Sport of Storytelling™ Open Mic with the Urban Wilderness Project ', 'Poets, Storytellers, Spoken Word, and Hip Hop Artists join together to form a performance team! The Game is played in rounds and each team gets scored by judges from the audience! Boost your teams score by dribbling, passing, or hooping the basketball&amp;mdash;that&amp;rsquo;s why we call it BoUnce!&amp;trade; Audience members enjoy a taste of every flavor of the oral traditions! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;First Fridays&lt;br /&gt;A new venue each month&lt;br /&gt;Call the BoUnce&amp;trade; Hotline &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;206-464-8364&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Or go to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/urbanwildernessproject&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;www.myspace.com/urbanwildernessproject&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Sign-up/Warm-up starts at 6 pm&lt;br /&gt;Game time 7 pm&lt;br /&gt;FEBRUARY 6, 2009 KICKOFF LOCATION&lt;br /&gt;Rainier Beach Community Center @&lt;br /&gt;Rainier Ave S. and Henderson&lt;br /&gt;Suggested Donation $1-5  NO ONE TURNED AWAY!!!!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Urban Wilderness Project is a Seattle non-profit who works to connect community, culture and the environment while creating tools for dismantling systematic oppressions and building inclusive and cooperative systems. urbanwildernessproject.org ', 0, 0, 0, 5, 1, '0[8X', ''),
(1444, 2454875, 2454875, '17:00:00', '20:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'R U An Endangered Species?™: Strange Fruit: Race, Violence and Environment Workshop presented by Urban Wilderness Project ', 'For many communities the violence of racial hatred committed in the woods still echoes through our collective memories. This post traumatic stress negatively impacts our relationships to the earth and to one another. Collectively we remain disconnected from the benefits of the outdoors which results in multiple threats to our physical and mental health, including obesity, diabetes, stress, and no relief from ADD and ADHD. The health of our communities and our youth depends on creating safe experiences for them to thrive, including the woods. Through truth, reconciliation and empowerment we can find solutions for healing our attitudes towards to the woods.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;http://urbanwildernessproject.org/spacer.gif&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Join us for this community conversation with Theryn B. Kigvamasud&#039;Vashti of CARA, Delbert Richardson, collector of the American History Exhibit: The Unspoken Truth, performances by Griot WorksýYouth Troupe, a. k. Allin, and host Jourdan I Keith. Learn what you can do to protect our social and natural Eco-systems.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Where:&lt;/strong&gt; Pritchard Beach Bathhouse, 8400 55th Avenue S.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cost:&lt;/strong&gt;  FREE ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
