(1458, 2454899, 2454899, '16:30:00', '17:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'VerleeRose CD Release Show ', 'VerleeRose CD Release ShowSun March 8th, 3pm&lt;br /&gt;With Special Guests...Shotty, Whitney Ballen &amp; Candysound&lt;br /&gt;$6 Adv. $8 Door&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.brownpapertickets.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#de7008&quot;&gt;http://www.brownpapertickets.com/&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; All Ages, Bar w/ID&lt;br /&gt;Columbia City Theater4916 Rainier Ave S.Seattle, WA 98118&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/verleerose&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#de7008&quot;&gt;www.myspace.com/verleerose&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;VerleeRose is 15 yr old Keira Verlee and 14 yr old Ellie Rose. An acoustic indie/pop singer/songwriter duo creating infectious hooks with thoughtful lyrics and incredible vocal harmonies that will get pleasantly stuck in your head for days. Across generations they are being compared to Tegan &amp; Sara meets the Indigo Girls although they are distinctly different than both of these duos.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At a very young age artists like Hilary Duff, Christina Aguilera and The Spice Girls inspired both girls to take piano and voice lessons. Now their inspiration comes from bands like The Beatles, Tegan &amp; Sara, Death Cab for Cutie, Anna Nalick, KT Tunstall, The New Pornographers, Regina Spektor, Coldplay and many more.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;They met each other as new 6th grade students at a Seattle-area middle school in 2005. The foundation for their friendship was built upon their shared love of music and history of piano and voice lessons. It was at this time that they declared they would someday make music together.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In May of 2008 the girls were given the opportunity to perform a song at their upcoming graduation. In two weeks time, they wrote, rehearsed and performed their first song for their graduating class. They were a roaring success and received a standing ovation from the audience! In this moment, VerleeRose was born.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In July a studio recording for a demo was offered to them if they could produce 3 songs by the end of the summer. In September of 2008 they started recording and finished in December with 9 original tracks. These songs plus two remixes were released on March 8, 2009 as their debut full length CD titled, These Moments. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(1453, 2454892, 2454892, '19:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Benefit Show for Community Alliance for Global Justice (CAGJ) ', '&lt;strong&gt;Sunday March 1st, 7 - 10pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Come enjoy groovy tunes &amp; good vibes &amp; help CAGJ raise crucial funds for 2009 organizing!&lt;br /&gt; Bring your friends!!&lt;br /&gt; @ Nectar Lounge&lt;br /&gt;412 N 36th St.  in Fremont&lt;br /&gt;featuring &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(255,0,0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ruby Shuz &amp; SUPERSONES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;$7 suggested donation (not one turned away)&lt;br /&gt; Address: 412 N. 36th St., Seattle WA 98103&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;SuperSones play the sublime music known as Son - the acoustic dance music of the Cuban countryside that inspired modern Salsa. Son is a unique blend of Spanish guitars and harmony, Afro-Cuban percussion and swing, call-and-response singing, and trumpet improvisation. From the 1930&amp;rsquo;s in Havana to the present moment, Cuban septets like SuperSones have inspired people around the world to dance and celebrate.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ruby Shuz just released their first CD &amp;ndash; check it out! Ruby Shuz vs. The Evil Doctor Frontenac (rubyshuz.com/music/)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Alliance for Global Justice&lt;/strong&gt; aims to transform the global economy by identifying local and global impacts of trade and monetary institutions, by using education, grassroots mobilization, media and legislative strategies, and by building solidarity across diverse movements.&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(1450, 2454877, 2454877, '15:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Saturday Food Not Bombs ', '&amp;ldquo;Free Food for Free People&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Saturday Feed at Westlake Center&lt;br /&gt;Come and eat wonderful free vegan food!&lt;br /&gt;We cook in the U District at about 10:00 and start feeding around 2:00 or 3:00.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://img8.imageshack.us/img8/3479/800foodnotbombs2cb8.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip;Because food is a human right, not a luxury. Because those we elect cannot guarantee us this most basic need for survival - and because we believe in building a community where people precede money, where gardens replace factory farms, and the where the soup is still hot. Look at all this wonderful food your friends have made for you!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We need plenty of help with food collection, cooking, serving and transportation for this and future feeds.&lt;br /&gt;Get involved at: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scn.org/foodnotbombs&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;www.scn.org/foodnotbombs&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Or e-mail us at: seattlefnb AT riseup DOT net ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[4X', ''),
(1451, 2454893, 2454893, '09:00:00', '13:00:00', 'Weeks', 1, 'Sustainable Small Acreage Farming and Ranching Course ', '&lt;img src=&quot;http://americanhistory.si.edu/militaryhistory/img/graphics/1574_l.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Dates&lt;/strong&gt;: Mondays, March 2, 9, 16&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time&lt;/strong&gt;: 9:00am-1:00pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Three different Vashon Island farms&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cost&lt;/strong&gt;: $15 for whole series for Vashon Island  Growers Association (VIGA) members, $30 for general public. Memberships available at registration. (Individual classes available for $10 VIGA and $20 for general public.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registration&lt;/strong&gt;: To register or for more information contact Joanne Jewell at &lt;a&gt;farmersmarket@vigavashon.org&lt;/a&gt; or call 206-267-8146.  Courses can be taken individually. Class size is limited to the indoor space available.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Vashon Island Growers Association (VIGA), King County Cooperative Extension, and Washington State University Puyallup, will be offering a series of three classes for farmers on Vashon Island.  This is a short version of the well-received WSU &quot;Cultivating Success&quot; course. The classes will have a hands-on component and will be held Monday mornings from 9am-1pm.  They will be taught by WSU Instructor/Commercial Farmer Clayton Burrows and WSU Soil Scientist Doug Collins with input from island farmers.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Learn practical information about whole farm planning, ecologically-based, diversified production systems, composting, soil management and marketing techniques. The course includes classroom discussion, research based information about farming from agricultural professionals, and tours of three island farms led by the farmers.  Class size is limited to indoor space available.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;March 2&lt;/strong&gt;: Sustainable Crop Production/Whole Farm Management&lt;br /&gt;              Plum Forest Farm, Paradise Valley&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;March 9&lt;/strong&gt;: Ecological Soil Management/Composting&lt;br /&gt;              Shoulder to Shoulder Farm, near Vashon town&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;March 16&lt;/strong&gt;: Profitability of Specific Crops for Small Farms&lt;br /&gt;                Hogsback Farm, Dilworth&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Course covers topics ranging from:&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip; Whole farm planning&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip; Soil biology &amp; management&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip; Pest &amp; weed management&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip; Profitability of specific crops&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip; Assessing resources &amp; market opportunities&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip; Evaluating personal &amp; family goals&lt;br /&gt;&amp;hellip; Accessing information &amp; community resources&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;How to get to Vashon Island from Seattle:&lt;br /&gt;Ferry schedule from West Seattle: http://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/schedules/current/index.cfm?route=f-v&lt;br /&gt;Take Route 54 of Seattle Metro toward West Seattle to get to the ferry terminal. Hitching is easy on the island, or take the bus on Saturdays (http://transit.metrokc.gov/tops/bus/schedules/s118_1_.html) ', 0, 3, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1452, 2454882, 2454882, '19:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Mexico Unconquered: Chronicles of Power and Revolt @ Central Cinema ', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAGJ Event Thursday February 19, 2009, 7 - 10pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;@ Central Cinema in the Central District&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FREE!!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://mexicounconquered.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/img_9854.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mexico Unconquered: Join us for an evening of music, film, photos and discussion!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Journalist and activist John Gibler will give a short talk about his new book, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Mexico Unconquered: Chronicles of Power and Revolt&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;, City Lights Books, 2009.   &amp;ldquo;Mexico Unconquered is an evocative report on the epic powers of violence and corruption in Mexico and the underdogs and rebels who put their lives on the line to build justice from the ground up.&amp;rdquo;  At the event we will watch a clip from the documentary, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;Un Poquito de Tanto Verdad&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo;When the people of Oaxaca decided they&amp;rsquo;d had enough of bad government, they didn&amp;rsquo;t take their story to the media&amp;hellip;they TOOK the media&amp;rdquo;; Film-maker Jill Friedberg in attendance; &lt;strong&gt;Photo Exhibit: 2007 Oaxaca Uprising and the Zapatista Other Campaign; Music by Correo Aereo and Sin Fronteras&lt;/strong&gt;. Food &amp; Drink available!  Admission FREE.  Location: Central Cinema @ 21st &amp; Union, 1411 21st Avenue, Seattle WA 98122 www.central-cinema.com&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(255,255,255);&quot;&gt;spacer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mexico No Conquistado: ¡Acompáñanos en una tarde de música, película, fotos y diálogo!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; El periodista y activista John Gibler hará una breve presentación sobre su libro, &amp;ldquo;El México No Conquistado: Crónicas de Poder y Rebelión&amp;rdquo;, publicado por City Light Books, 2009. &amp;ldquo;México No Conquistado es un reportaje evocativo sobre los poderes épicos de la violencia y la corrupción en México y sobre la gente común y los rebeldes que arriesgan su vida en su afán de construir la justicia desde los cimientos.&amp;rdquo; En este evento se exibirá también una sinopsis del documental &amp;ldquo;Un Poquito de Tanta Verdad&amp;rdquo;&amp;hellip; &amp;ldquo;Cuando la gente de Oaxaca decidió que ya estaban hartos de tanto mal gobierno, no fueron a hacer sus denuncias a los medios de comunicación&amp;hellip; se TOMARON los medios de comunicación&amp;rdquo;; la cineasta Jill Friedberg estará en el evento. También disfruta de una exibición de fotografías sobre el Levantamiento de Oaxaca del 2007 y sobre la Otra Campaña de los Zapatistas, de la música de Correo Aereo y Sin Fronteras, además de bocadillos y refrescos. Admisión GRATUÍTA. Jueves 19 de Febrero, 7 &amp;ndash; 10 pm. En el Central Cinema @ 21st &amp; Union, 1411 21st Avenue, Seattle WA 98122, www.central-cinema.comCo-auspiciado por Community Alliance for Global Justice. Para mayor información, llama al 206.405.4600 o email a contact_us@seattleglobaljustice.org&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(1454, 2454912, 2454912, '13:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Grafting Workshop on Vashon Island ', '&lt;img src=&quot;http://julieluongo.files.wordpress.com/2007/02/olbinski-apple-trees-33607.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Saturday, March 21st at 1:00 pm&lt;br /&gt;Vashon Fruit Club - Grafting Workshop&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;at Bruce Jackson&#039;s orchard&lt;br /&gt;17920 94th Ave SW on Vashon Island&lt;br /&gt;Enter from Bank Road east of town and drive to the end of 94th Ave SW.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Other workshops in this series:&lt;br /&gt;Tuesday, April 14th at 7:00 pm, our quarterly business meeting, followed by&lt;br /&gt;an intro to pest and disease control in the orchard.  Courthouse Square&lt;br /&gt;meeting room.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Sunday, April 19th at 1:00 pm, a panel discussion on pest and disease&lt;br /&gt;control.  Courthouse Square meeting room.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The classes are for members of the club. The annual membership fee is just $20 &amp; gets you access to all workshops.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;How to get to Vashon Island from Seattle:&lt;br /&gt;Ferry schedule from West Seattle: http://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/schedules/current/index.cfm?route=f-v&lt;br /&gt;Take Route 54 of Seattle Metro toward West Seattle to get to the ferry terminal. Hitching is easy on the island, or take the bus on Saturdays&lt;br /&gt;(http://transit.metrokc.gov/tops/bus/schedules/s118_1_.html) ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
