(1478, 2454895, 2454895, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Queer Film Night Seattle! ', '&lt;img src=&quot;http://profile.ak.facebook.com/object3/1356/72/n67227097743_9668.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;First queer film night happening on March 4th. Join us at 8 PM, March 4th. Corner of MLK/John. E-mail aplacecalledyes@gmail.com for more details or join FB group. We&#039;re on Facebook as a group, do a search for &quot;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Queer Film Night Seattle&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;!&quot; and join in if you&#039;re into that sort of thing. There&#039;s a schedule of movies up there as well. We provide hella popcorn, you provide things to drink and if you want, other snacks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Film for March 4 is &lt;strong&gt;Victim&lt;/strong&gt; (Basil Dearden, 1961, UK). &quot;Dirk Bogarde stars as Melville Farr, a married, successful, closeted gay barister. After his lover is killed, Farr puts his marriage, career and life on the line by deciding to find the killers and fight back.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot; color=&quot;#ff0000&quot;&gt;Everyone is welcome! &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(1471, 2454896, 2454896, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'bodylove @ richard hugo house ', 'SHIFT Peer Recovery Network and TumbleMe Productions Present:&lt;br /&gt; ** BODYLOVE: QUEER BODIES REVEALED THROUGH THE SPOKEN WORD! **&lt;br /&gt; In Celebration of National &lt;span&gt;Eating Disorders Awareness Week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;March 5th, 2009&lt;/span&gt;, doors 7:30 p.m., show 8:00 p.m.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span&gt;Richard Hugo&lt;/span&gt; House&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;1634 11th Avenue&lt;br /&gt; Seattle, WA 98122&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;206-322-7030&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; $5 cover.  All proceeds go to &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;National Eating Disorders Association&lt;/span&gt;, &quot;dedicated to providing education, resources and support to those affected by eating disorders.&quot;  A donation large or small gives the gift of support &amp; recovery to those who need it!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; BODYLOVE: QUEER BODIES REVEALED THROUGH THE SPOKEN WORD! BodyLove will open your eyes and your heart, as 10 talented and distinct writers take the stage to REVEAL untold stories about queer bodies.  A benefit show for National Eating Disorders Association, BodyLove will take you on a journey through the PAIN, SHAME, RECOVERY and liberation of &quot;the tyranny of thin,&quot; and other battles with &lt;span&gt;body image&lt;/span&gt; and eating addiction/disorders.  But don&#039;t forget the LOVE! The evening will also celebrate the beauty and BOUNTY of bodies, flaunting who we are and entertaining the outrageous notion that what we&#039;ve got is SUPER HOT.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; THE PERFORMERS:&lt;br /&gt; The line-up includes artists who are gaining international recognition and funding for their work. Chad Goller-Sojourner will perform excerpts of his award-winning one-man show, &quot;Sitting in Circles With &lt;span&gt;Rich Girls&lt;/span&gt;: Memoirs Of A Bulimic Black Boy.&quot;   Amber Flame, a nationally touring word artist and author of one-woman show SKINSTORIES &amp; OTHER HALF-TRUTHS  will also grace the stage.  If that&#039;s not enough to whet your appetite, check out the whole line-up:&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; ELAINA M. ELLIS &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/watch?v&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ANW1AmKja8w&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt; CHAD GOLLER-SOJOURNER: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.goller-sojourner.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;http://www.goller-sojourner.com/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt; AMBER FLAME: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/a_flame&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;www.myspace.com/a_flame&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt; PATCH AVERY; SANDI STREHLAU; TOBY LANGFORD; PIDGE BLANKS; MARITA&lt;br /&gt; DELEON TERRY; CORINNE SCHNEIDER; AUTUMN K. DIAL&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; SHIFT is a Peer Recovery Network supporting dynamic recovery paths by uniting our LGBTQ community to experience freedom through empowerment.  A collaboration between Multifaith Works, &lt;span&gt;Seattle&lt;/span&gt; Counseling Service, Gay City, &amp; Dunshee House. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(1515, 2454892, 2455196, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Floating', 1, 'Sew Up Seattle classes! ', '&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Sew Up Seattle is a sewing recycling adventure. Since 1997 we have been gathering, gleaning, sharing and re-purposing donated fabric scraps, notions and equipment. No scrap is too small!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Free sewing classes are held on the last Saturday of the month, most months, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;at &lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);&quot;&gt;Goods for the Planet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;525 Dexter Avenue North&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Seattle, Wash. 98109&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;For information, or to register, call &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);&quot;&gt;206-784-7117&lt;/span&gt;, or email &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);&quot;&gt;sewupseattle@yahoo.com&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,153,0);font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(51,204,0);&quot;&gt;Space is limited and we don&#039;t want you to be disappointed! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(51,204,0);&quot;&gt;Please do call 