(1472, 2454883, 2454885, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Seattle Improvised Music Festival, weekend 2 ', 'Now in its 24th year, the &lt;strong&gt;Seattle Improvised Music Festival&lt;/strong&gt; will be held February 13, 14, 15, 20, 21 and 22, 2008 at &lt;a href=&quot;http://gschapel.blogspot.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Chapel Performance Space&lt;/a&gt; (Wallingford) and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.gallery1412.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Gallery 1412&lt;/a&gt; (at 18th and Union on Capitol Hill). &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The longest running festival of its kind in North America, SIMF is an annual meeting place for improvisers at the forefront of Improvised Music in North America, and from around the world.&lt;br /&gt;This year&#039;s festival features representatives of improvised music communities in &lt;strong&gt;Lebanon, France, Berlin, NYC, Massachusetts, Connecticut, San Diego, Portland,&lt;/strong&gt; and of course &lt;strong&gt;Seattle&lt;/strong&gt;. The festival includes showcased performances from visiting soloists and ensembles while also featuring first-time collaborations between festival performers.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;friday 2-20 (chapel)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;(1)&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;International Nothing&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;Kai Fagaschinski / Michael Thieke&lt;/strong&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;(2)&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;rachel thompson / jonathan zorn&lt;/strong&gt; duo&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;(3)&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Le Quan Ninh / special guest&lt;/strong&gt; duo &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;saturday 2-21 12:00 pm (gallery 1412)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;improvised music workshop&lt;/strong&gt; - free!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;saturday 2-21 (chapel)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;(1)&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Le Quan Ninh&lt;/strong&gt; solo, &lt;strong&gt;special guest&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;/ andrew drury / tar