(1479, 2454912, 2454912, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Food Not Bombs: Building Community - an Evening with Keith McHenry ', '&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Food Not Bombs: Building Community - an Evening with Keith McHenry&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Saturday, March 21st&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;7pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Rainier Valley Unitarian Universalist Center &amp;ndash; 835 Yesler Way, Seattle, Wa 98104&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Keith McHenry, co-founder of the international peace and social change movement Food Not Bombs will be speaking at the Rainier Valley Unitarian Universalist Center (835 Yesler Way) March 21 at 7PM.  His talk on the history and the upcoming 30th anniversary of Food not Bombs will be accompanied by a vegan potluck -- please bring a dish to share.     &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Food not Bombs has active groups throughout the Americas, Europe, Africa, the Middle East, Asia and Australia.  It is an all-volunteer organization dedicated to nonviolent social change. There are no formal leaders and FNB strives to include everyone in its decision making process. Each group recovers food that would otherwise be thrown out and distributes it to people in need or makes fresh hot vegetarian meals that are served outdoors in public spaces. Food not Bombs also caters social change events, protests and actions.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;For more information:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font