(1481, 2454905, 2454905, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'VEGAN PROM for the AETA 4 ', '&lt;strong&gt;Where:&lt;/strong&gt; Skin Deep Studios&amp;ndash;&lt;a href=&quot;http://maps.google.com/maps?f&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0066cc&quot;&gt;2524 16th Ave S #311, Seattle&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (inside the big community center El Centro de la Raza) &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;On February 20, 2009, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.greenisthenewred.com/blog/2009/02/22/aeta-arrests/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#b85b5a&quot;&gt;four animal rights activists &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;were arrested under the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.greenisthenewred.com/blog/2007/11/17/aeta-101/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#b85b5a&quot;&gt;Animal Enterprise Terrorism Act&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Their alleged crimes include protesting and publishing the contact information of vivisectors&amp;mdash;activities. protected by the First Amendment. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.narn.org/index.php&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#b85b5a&quot;&gt;Northwest Animal Rights Network&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is hosting a vegan prom to raise funds for their legal defense. So dust off your tuxedo, hit the thrift store for a cocktail dress, and stand up for freedom of speech! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://i409.photobucket.com/albums/pp172/thisforever/aeta4-1.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Music by DJ Coldheart &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talks by Darius Fullmer, SHAC7 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;and Jenn Kaplan, Animal Rights Lawyer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;$15 includes vegan taco bar &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RSVP at &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;www.narn.org/aeta4&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0066cc&quot;&gt;www.narn.org/aeta4&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note: The venue requests that attendees remove their shoes to protect the floors. Bring your slippers!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bus directions:&lt;/strong&gt; Depart 3rd Ave &amp; Union St At 7:35 PM On Route MT 36 Rainier Beach.  Arrive Beacon Ave S &amp; S Bayview St At 7:52 PM.  Walk 0.1 mile E to 2524 16TH AVE S.  &lt;strong&gt;Driving directions:  *&lt;/strong&gt;From downtown, turn LEFT (east) onto Jackson St.  *Turn RIGHT (south) onto 12th Ave S.  *12th Ave S turns into 14th Ave S.  *Turn LEFT onto Beacon Ave S.  *Turn LEFT onto S Lander St (across from Red Apple Market).  *Entrance is the driveway on the right just before S Bayview St.  *Go into the very large community center building. *Look for &amp;ldquo;Vegan Prom&amp;rdquo; signs pointing the way.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
