(1486, 2454896, 2454896, '16:30:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Lecture on the Oaxaca Social Movement 2006-present ', '226 Communication Hall, UW Campus - 4:30 PM - 6:30 PM&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Lynn Stephen- Testimony, Political Culture, and Claims for Rights: The Oaxaca Social Movement 2006-present&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; This study explores acts of testimony and their links to global discourses of human, women&#039;s, and Indigenous rights in the southern Mexican state of Oaxaca. The testimonials here are urgent oral accounts of bearing witness to wrongs committed against the speakers. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Broadcast on the radio, television, at public demonstrations, and in the street, testimonial rights claiming in Oaxaca repositions previously excluded speakers as active citizens. &lt;br /&gt;This project centers on a recent and ongoing social movement in Oaxaca, Mexico and the emergence in June, 2006 of the Popular Assembly of the Peoples of Oaxaca (APPO), that effectively ran the city for six months until the Mexican federal police force intervened. &lt;br /&gt;Testimony and rights claiming occupy central roles in this complex context, permitting silenced groups to speak, be heard, and enact alternative visions for political and cultural participation. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This project will result in a book and public access website about how people in local communities appropriate rights ideas, fuse them with oral testimonials, and reframe them to fit their own systems of cultural meanings and particular political circumstances. &lt;br /&gt;At a larger level this project will do much to shed light on: 1) contemporary processes of ethnic, racial, and gendered identity formation and rights claiming, 2) definitions of participatory democracy, political society, and citizenship, and 3) models for achieving cultural dialogue across different groups. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(1487, 2454903, 2454903, '18:00:00', '19:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'Sense &amp; Sustainability @ the Capitol Hill Library ', '&lt;font style=&quot;background-color:#ffff66&quot;&gt;THE CITY WANTS TO GIVE YOU MONEY TO MAKE STUFF. Come find out how you can get money from the city for building a P-Patch, planting free trees, or creating public art in your neighborhood. Allynn Ruth from the City of Seattle Department of Neighborhoods will be leading us through the process of applying for small and large funds and answering audience questions. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color:#ffff66&quot; size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;Free and open to all, plus there will be juice.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;WHEN: &lt;br /&gt;March 12, 6-7:30pm&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;WHERE:&lt;br /&gt;Capitol Hill branch&lt;br /&gt;Seattle Public Library&lt;br /&gt;425 Harvard Ave E.&lt;br /&gt;Call 206-684-4715 with any questions&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;background-color:#ffff66&quot;&gt;This is part of a group of events we&#039;re calling Sense &amp; Sustainability (a little Jane A. nod there) - we&#039;re going to have workshops on preparing cheap good food, personal finances, and other goodies. Go to your local library!&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1488, 2454938, 2454938, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Music Theory Skill-Share @ Artic Circle. ', '&lt;img src=&quot;http://i471.photobucket.com/albums/rr72/seattleestateauctions/misc/IMG_1527_small.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Arctic Circle (a house in Georgetown) will be hosting a series of skill-shares &amp; this is the first installment!! Neil will be sharing all he knows about music and the theory behind it. Learn how to read, write, and/or deconstruct music!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;6633 Ellis Ave S&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;April 16&lt;br /&gt;8:00 PM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Snacks and/or donations will always be welcome, but don&#039;t feel obligated.  We&#039;re more interested in seeing you there!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;email Neil at neil [at] pirateandcowboy.com with questions. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(1489, 2454904, 2454904, '17:00:00', '19:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Beehive Collective at the UW Seattle! ', '&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;The BEEHIVE COLLECTIVE is coming to UW Seattle!  &lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Friday March 13, 2009, from 5-7pm&lt;br /&gt;Ethnic Cultural Center @ 3931 Brooklyn Ave NE&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; contact aark@u.washington.edu&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In eager anticipation of the new life spring promises the&lt;strong&gt; Beehive Collective is coming to UW Seattle to present their new graphic campaign, The TRUE COST OF COAL. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We&#039;d love to see you there! March 13, 5-7pm,&lt;/strong&gt; with snacks to keep our energy up till evening! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://beehivecollective.org/&quot;&gt;beehivecollective.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;  &lt;br /&gt;Here&#039;s some information about the Current Campaign:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The Beehive&#039;s newest graphic - the TRUE COST OF COAL (in the works, nearly complete!) - uses mountaintop removal in Appalachia as a lens through which to understand the historical and contemporary story of ENERGY, RESOURCE EXTRACTION, and of AMERICAN EMPIRE accelerating throughout the world. It seeks to expose the DECEPTIONS of CLEAN COAL technologies and bring to light the ensuing CLIMATE CHAOS facing the world today. This graphic also looks to the future, raising questions about RESISTANCE, REGENERATION, and REMEDIATION while celebrating stories of struggle from mountain communities. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
