(1500, 2454932, 2454934, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Honk! Fest West 2009 ', 'WHAT: Honk! Fest West 2009 &lt;p&gt;WHEN: April 10 &amp;ndash; 12, 2009&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;WHERE: Venues and streets of Ballard and Georgetown&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;DESCRIPTION: Honk!Fest West, a Vera Sponsored Project, returns to Seattle this year April 10 -12. Honk!Fest West, the northwest counterpart to the 3 day brass band festival founded in Somerville, MA, is a celebration of the music of street bands from around the world. This year over 15 bands from around the continent will join in the festivities, including Stanford University&amp;rsquo;s nationally-acclaimed scatter band. Honk!Fest West begins Friday, April 10th in Ballard, venues in Georgetown Saturday evening, a brunch potluck at Gasworks Park Sunday afternoon, and culminates in an all-band line up at The Vera Project.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The event will also feature workshops throughout the weekend with members of Seattle&amp;rsquo;s vibrant musical community. The Seattle Seahawks Blue Thunder Drumline and the Seattle Sounders FC Sound Wave Band will also be performing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A full list of bands, line-up and venue information can be found at &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.honkfestwest.com/&quot;&gt;honkfestwest.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Media Contact:&lt;br /&gt; Grace Kuan&lt;br /&gt; &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;mailto:honkwest@gmail.com&quot;&gt;honkwest@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt; 206-427-3056&lt;/p&gt; ', 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(1518, 2454920, 2454920, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Weeks', 1, 'Food Not Bombs ', '&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;font-size:14px;-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing:1px;-webkit-border-vertical-spacing:1px;&quot;&gt;Every &lt;strong&gt;Sunday&lt;/strong&gt; evening around &lt;strong&gt;6pm&lt;/strong&gt;, Food Not Bombs shares a free veggie meal open to everyone at Occidental Park (in Pioneer Square). We start cooking at about &lt;strong&gt;1:30pm Sunday&lt;/strong&gt; afternoon at &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.cascadepeoplescenter.org/&quot;&gt;Cascade People&amp;rsquo;s Center &lt;/a&gt;&lt;a&gt;at 309 Pontius Avenue North, Seattle, WA 98109 - Phone: (206)587-0320. To get involved in the cooking, cleaning, serving or food collection, leave a message at &lt;strong&gt;(206) 949-0322&lt;/strong&gt;, email &lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:seattle-fnb@riseup.net&quot;&gt;seattle-fnb@riseup.net&lt;/a&gt;. or stop by Occidental Park Sunday evening, we&#039;d love to meet you.&lt;/span&gt; ', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[4X', ''),
(1502, 2454905, 2454905, '14:00:00', '16:30:00', 'Weeks', 1, 'contact improv class! ', 'Contact Improvisation is a contemporary dance form that involves interdependence with a partner as well as individual balance and strength. It teaches dancers to interact with the everyday physical world in an intentional, physically present manner. I will teach a 3-meeting contact improv class, with two sections. The first section will meet Wednesdays, March 11, 18, and 25 from 2-4:30pm. The second section will meet Saturdays March 14 and 21 from 2-4:30 pm, and March 28 from 12-2:30pm. The Saturday class is basically a repeat of the Wednesdays, so people can choose whether they want to do Wednesdays or Saturdays. This is for beginners or experienced contact dancers. People don&#039;t have to attend all three classes to take any, though it will be a series. The tuition is a suggested donation of $10/class. Location: Sukha Yoga dance studio, 224 minor ave N, apt B (near REI, across from cascade people&#039;s center). for more info contact (heh heh) raccooncarobtree@yahoo.com ', 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1516, 2454925, 2454925, '19:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, '@ Q Cafe: Film Screening - Call &amp; Response ', 'Call and Response is a landmark advocacy film documenting the state of slavery in our world today: 27 million men, women, and (mostly) children who are currently slaves.  A host of celebrities explain what&#039;s going on, and how we can act.&lt;P /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;On April 3, Q Cafe will co-host a film screening, paired with a chance for people to speak directly with local groups involved in ending global slavery.  The film screening will start at 7pm, followed by an advocacy fair with representatives from HEAL Africa, World Concern, Call and Response, and the SOLD Project.&lt;P /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Q Cafe 3223 15th Ave. W. Seattle, WA 98119, www.qcafe.org ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
