(1573, 2454930, 2454930, '18:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Anti-Racist Whites For Immigrant Rights! ', '&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anti-Racist Whites For Immigrant Rights!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Coalition of Anti-Racist Whites invites you to a workshop that will explore immigration history and analysis of race, class and whiteness as they influence immigration politics and policies.  Best of all, we&amp;rsquo;ll present practical ways white people can advocate for improvements in immigrant rights within our own communities.  The material for this workshop is designed for white folks who are interested in examining privilege and building skills given their positionalitiy.  All people are welcome to attend.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Immigrant Ally Workshop&lt;br /&gt;Wednesday April 8th&lt;br /&gt;6 pm potluck&lt;br /&gt;6:30-8:30 activities and discussion&lt;br /&gt;Cascade People&amp;rsquo;s Center ~ 309 Pontius Ave N (near REI)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;CARW is a group of white people in the Seattle area working to undo institutional racism and white privilege through education and organizing in white communities while actively supporting people of color-led organizations. This workshop is part of our current campaign with El Comité Pro-Reforma Migratoria y Justica Social (a grassroots Latina/o-led immigrant and worker rights group in Seattle).  CARW supports the self-determination of people of color, honor their leadership and are held accountable to people of color-led organizations.  More info at http://carw.org/ ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(1575, 2454925, 2454925, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Br&#039;er, Corespondents, The Toy Boats, Julie Baldrich, a slide show by Ilvs Strauss, Banana Bread Bake Off! at the Office of Dr. Glorious ', '&lt;a href=&quot;http://viewmorepics.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://hotlink.myspacecdn.com/images02/102/5d97f5f7f9534e129972a2a9ea3e4448/m.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Office of Doctor Glorious is proud to present:&lt;br /&gt;Br&#039;er who hail all the way from the great city of Philadelphia, you can hear them at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.msplinks.com/MDFodHRwOi8vd3d3LmZ1bGxncm93bm1hbi5jb20&quot;&gt;www.fullgrownman.com&lt;/a&gt; or look them up on myspace. The Toy Boats, whom I haven&#039;t yet seen these folks live but judging by the members this should be amazing. Anne (Infernal Noise, Orkestar Zirkonium) and her partner Steve (Infernal Noise and an amazing concertina player) are both in this band. They play old songs on toy instruments &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/thetoyboatsband&quot;&gt;www.myspace.com/thetoyboatsband&lt;/a&gt;. The always amazing Corespondents will also be joining us again. They played here once before but have since changed the direction of their sound to include percussion and other wiley sounds. You can check them out at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.msplinks.com/MDFodHRwOi8vY29yZXNwb25kZW50cy5vcmc&quot;&gt;corespondents.org&lt;/a&gt; or also here on myspace. There will also be a banana bread bake off, between Karolina and Allan. This battle has been a long time in the making with much shit talking taking place along the way. This should get heated. Come out, get free banana bread and pick the new banana bread queen of the 22nd and Fir corridor. Just added to the show is the amazing Julie Baldrich (Sugar Skulls and others). If you like the violin and have never seen her play than this is a must see.  Another last minute addition is that Ilvs Strauss will be providing us with some of her amazing slide shows between bands. I promise she will blow you away! The Office of Dr. Glorious is located at 2216 E. Fir St. in the Central District. The show starts promptly at 8pm and costs $4 for the touring band. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(1576, 2454930, 2454930, '20:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Jason Kahn / Christopher DeLaurenti @ gallery 1412 ', '&lt;font color=&quot;#7f7f00&quot; size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Seattle Improvised Music presents:&lt;br /&gt;Jason Kahn; Christopher DeLaurenti&lt;/font&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;+0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;jason kahn&lt;/strong&gt;  (zurich);&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;chrisopher delaurenti&lt;/strong&gt;  (seattle)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;set one:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jason Kahn / Gust Burns&lt;/strong&gt;:  percussion/synth - inside piano  duo&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;set two:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Christopher DeLaurenti&lt;/strong&gt; - flap-o-phone solo&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;set three:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jason Kahn&lt;/strong&gt; leads quartet with:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mara Sedlins&lt;/strong&gt; (viola), &lt;strong&gt;Wilson Shook&lt;/strong&gt; (alto saxophone), &lt;strong&gt;Gust Burns&lt;/strong&gt; (inside piano)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;+0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Jason Kahn&lt;/strong&gt;&#039;s work includes sound installation, performance and composition. He was born in New York in 1960, grew up in Los Angeles and relocated to Europe in 1990. He currently lives in Zürich.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;He has given concerts and exhibited sound installations throughout Europe, North and South America, Japan, Mexico, Korea, Israel, Turkey, Russia, Lebanon, Egypt, Hong Kong, New Zealand and Australia.  Kahn performs both solo and in collaborations, using percussion, analog synthesizer or computer in different combinations.  He composes for electronics, acoustic instruments and environmental recordings. For larger groups of directed improvisation he has devised a system of graphical scores.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Kahn creates his sound installations for specific spaces. The focus of these primarily non-visual works lies in the perception of a space through sound.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;jasonkahn.net&lt;br /&gt;rasbliutto.net/artists/gustburns.html&lt;br /&gt;gallery1412.org/wilsonshook.html&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With a handmade cardboard turntable - the flap-o-phone - &lt;strong&gt;Christopher DeLaurenti&lt;/strong&gt; interprets the music of Maurice Ravel and Igor Stravinsky as preserved on 78 rpm records.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In these performances, acoustic and electronic become truly &quot;electroacoustic&quot; as variances in manual speed and unpredictable needle behavior (occasional skipping, skittering, and groove-rutting) as well as irregularities on the record surface and in the surrounding environment establish circular, self-reinforcing sonic relationships between player and playback; acoustic music and electronic performance; composed &quot;masterpieces&quot; and improvised uncertainty. Pieces to be performed at Gallery 1412 include the &quot;Piano-Rag Music&quot; of Stravinsky and Ravel&#039;s &quot;Bolero.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;delaurenti.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Gallery 1412&lt;br /&gt;1412 18th ave&lt;br /&gt;gallery1412.org&lt;/font&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
