(1579, 2454961, 2454961, '17:00:00', '21:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'The New Narrative: Local Voices for a Global Future ', 'The Global Oneness Project presents a series of free film events recognizing the role of local communities in global change. Join us to exchange ideas, foster relationships, and strengthen the changes already happening in our world.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Where: &lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;ý&quot;&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.seattlehistory.org/&quot;&gt;Museum of History and Industry&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/font&gt;, &lt;/font&gt;Located in  McCurdy Park at 2700 24th Ave. E&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Featuring:&lt;br /&gt;Short films from the Global Oneness Project&lt;br /&gt;Interactive cafe-style conversations &lt;br /&gt;Guest speaker Orland Bishop, founder of ShadeTree Multicultural Foundation in Watts, Los Angeles, and a pioneer of innovative approaches to urban truces and restoring community&lt;br /&gt;Q&amp;A with filmmaker Emmanuel Vaughan-Lee&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Global Oneness Project is documenting a growing understanding of what it means to be part of one interconnected, interdependent world. Since 2006, the Project has traveled to six continents, gathering stories from individuals and organizations working in the fields of sustainability, conflict resolution, social justice, spirituality, indigenous wisdom, and politics. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Participating Organizations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wiserearth.org/organization/view/89521c44db76ba600077a3d0c5064557&quot;&gt;Yes! Magazine&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wiserearth.org/organization/view/c888c077b70a22ac7450e40886d05460&quot;&gt;Worldchanging&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wiserearth.org/organization/view/baae8763db92e84a38139d2753a6718b&quot;&gt;Heritage Institute&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wiserearth.org/organization/view/f23986e941db5e17a1ff9ec95f979b73&quot;&gt;