(1590, 2454961, 2454961, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Classes at ZAPP (Zine Archive &amp; Publishing Project) ', '&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:georgia,timesnewroman,times,serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;ZAPP&lt;/span&gt;, Hugo House&#039;s Zine Archive and Publishing Project, offers occasional classes on zines, zine history and aspects of zine-making, led by local writers and artists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Teaching With Zines&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:georgia,timesnewroman,times,serif;&quot;&gt;We will explore zines as an educational tool: as texts, as a medium for self-expression, and as a method of teaching elements of existing curricula.  We will provide an overview of the history of zines and their defining characteristics, discuss various methods of zinemaking, and guide practical zinemaking exercises.  There will also be discussion about how zines can be incorporated into various educational settings, and how zines can be powerful tools for teaching students about media literacy, the importance of free expression, creative writing, craftsmanship, and many other topics.  Zinemaking materials will be provided.&lt;br /&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:georgia,timesnewroman,times,serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Instructors: &lt;/span&gt;Tyler Hauck and Emily Grayson&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Meets: &lt;/span&gt;May 9, 2009, 1:00-5:00 p.m. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Price:&lt;/span&gt; $40&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:georgia,timesnewroman,times,serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Middle School Zine-ster Double Feature: Words &amp; Pictures 5-Week Workshop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Anyone reading graphic novels, comics, magazine ads or surfing the Internet can attest that words and pictures make for a powerful combination.  Put their awesome combined forces to work for you as we create stories, collage, comics, poems, rants, recipes, you-name-it in this five week workshop, with the ultimate goal of creating one of the world&#039;s greatest communication tools: Your Own Zine.  &lt;span style=&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;*This class is for middle school students only. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Instructor: &lt;/span&gt;David Lasky &amp; Nora Mukihata&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Meets: &lt;/span&gt;Saturdays, May 2 ý 30, 10 a.m. ý 12 p.m.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:georgia,timesnewroman,times,serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Price:&lt;/span&gt; $50&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:georgia,timesnewroman,times,serif;&quot;&gt;To register, email Nora Mukaihata at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:noramukaihata@hugohouse.org&quot;&gt;noramukaihata@hugohouse.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:georgia,timesnewroman,times,serif;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;http://www.hugohouse.org/classes/zappclasses/ ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
