(1676, 2454971, 2454971, '19:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'LOST FILM FEST! ', 'Monsterssori Microcinema Presents:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Radical.&lt;br /&gt;Radically awesome.&lt;br /&gt;LOST FILM FEST&lt;br /&gt;MAY 19TH 7pm!  &lt;br /&gt;potluck at 7, films to promptly start at 8. &lt;br /&gt;2317 14th Ave S, Beacon Hill&lt;br /&gt;5-10 bux sliding scale for travelling Philidelphians&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;SURPRISE!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Surprise email!  Announcing a surprise show!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Monstersorri Microcinema&#039;s friends, West Philly&#039;s own LOST FILM FEST is coming to Seattle for one night to present a special show at the MONSTERSSORI OBSERVATORY.  Lost Film Fest is a sort of hilarious, politically and culturally radical, free-form short video festival where VJ Scotty Beibin sort of freeform-selects videos from his hard drive.  Scott works with some amazing people in his other life as part of Evil Twin Booking, so he&#039;s often got otherwise unavailable videos from such favorites as the YES MEN and others.  &lt;br /&gt;Scott also promises a special sneek preview of his new show, SCIENTISTS ARE THE NEW ROCK STARS: &quot;a live multimedia spectacle exploring the fuzzy and quarky lines between hard science, social science, and metaphysics with hands-on examples of environmentally sustainable art and technologies.&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;http://www.lostfilmfest.com/&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bring a friend!  This is a surprise show, surprise us with a great audience and we&#039;ll bring you more great stuff like this in the future!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Yours in Crime,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;AV Flaxoil&lt;br /&gt;Media Monopolist ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
