(1731, 2454993, 2454993, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'CARA benefit movie night at Cascade People&#039;s Center ', 'Please join the CARW CARA Campaign Committe in another Movie Night Fundraiser!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&quot;OUT: The Making of a &lt;span&gt;Revolutionary&lt;/span&gt;&quot;: &lt;br /&gt;a documentary of &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;Laura Whitehorn&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;br /&gt;anti-racist white lesbian and former &lt;span style=&quot;background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;political prisoner&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;Wednesday, June 10th, 2009 &lt;br /&gt;6:30pm&lt;/span&gt; potluck.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;7pm&lt;/span&gt; movie and discussion&lt;br /&gt;at Cascade People&#039;s Center&lt;br /&gt;(directions and busses below) &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cost: Sliding scale $5-25 &lt;br /&gt;(no one turned away for lack of funds)   &lt;br /&gt; all proceeds to benefit Communities Against Rape and Abuse&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cara-seattle.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;www.cara-seattle.org&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;movies details:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&quot;OUT: The Making of a Revolutionary&quot;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Directed by Sonja de Vries and Rhonda Collins &lt;br /&gt;(2000)  USA  60 min.  color  &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;Third World Newsreel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The recipient of audience awards in France and &lt;span style=&quot;background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;Germany&lt;/span&gt;, OUT: The Making of a &lt;br /&gt;Revolutionary (2000) is the story of Laura Whitehorn, an anti-racist white lesbian, who was convicted of the 1983 US Capitol bombing, and of &quot;conspiring to influence, change, and protest policies and practices of the United States government through violent and illegal means.&quot; One of six defendants in the Resistance Conspiracy Case, Whitehorn spent 14 years in prison for her radical leftist political stance. OUT is the story of her life and times: five tumultuous decades of &lt;span style=&quot;background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;struggle for freedom&lt;/span&gt; and justice. Whether you agree or disagree with radical left politics, this is a documentary that will challenge you to think about what you might be willing to risk for your own beliefs.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&quot;The film skillfully interpolates historical footage of a &#039;whites only&#039; world &lt;br /&gt;with the life story of an exceptionally engaging woman who was not only a &lt;br /&gt;revolutionary who acted on her principles, but also a lesbian.&quot;   -- &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);cursor:pointer;&quot;&gt;Bay Area &lt;br /&gt; Reporter&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&quot;Seeing OUT is worthwhile not only for progressive politicos, but for &lt;br /&gt;anyone who can  appreciate the story of a classic American type: the &lt;br /&gt;conscientious rebel.&quot;    -- &lt;span style=&quot;background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;San Francisco Express&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;directions:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cascade People&#039;s Center&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;433 Minor Avenue North&lt;br /&gt;Seattle, WA 98109&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Directions from I-5 North or South:&lt;br /&gt;Exit 167 off I-5, left onto Fairview Ave N, left at third light onto Thomas St, two blocks, left onto Pontius Ave N, the Center is first driveway on your left. We&amp;rsquo;re next to Cascade Park and the P-Patch, across the street from &lt;span&gt;Immanuel Lutheran Church&lt;/span&gt;. Tan building with red trim. Look for our brightly colored murals!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bus Routes&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;br /&gt;Bus Routes: 8, 25, 70-73, 74, 77, 79, 304, 317, 355, 377&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;for more info contact scott at &lt;span style=&quot;border-bottom:1pxdashedrgb(0,102,204);background:transparentnonerepeatscroll0%0%;cursor:pointer;-moz-background-clip:-moz-initial;-moz-background-origin:-moz-initial;-moz-background-inline-policy:-moz-initial;&quot;&gt;206-324-8165&lt;/span&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
