(1816, 2455038, 2455038, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Teach Out! Engaging the Local Food Cycle ', 'AN OPPORTUNITY TO LEARN ABOUT OUR LOCAL FOOD SYSTEM&lt;br /&gt; Coordinated by the Food Justice Project of the Community Alliance for Global Justice&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Third Event! Fisherman&#039;s Terminal, UDistrict Farmer&#039;s Market, UW Student farm and Cob Oven&lt;br /&gt; Saturday, July 25th, 11:30am-4:00pm (Bikers will meet at the Locks in Ballard at 11am)&lt;br /&gt; JOIN THE GUIDED BIKE RIDE, RIDE THE BUS, OR CAR-POOL!&lt;br /&gt; Requested donation $5.00&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We will begin our day with Hing Lau Ng of Loki Fish Company as she gives us a tour of Fisherman&#039;s Terminal and talks about current issues facing this important space in Seattle&#039;s local food system. Next, we will visit the University District Farmer&#039;s Market, one of the largest farmer&#039;s markets in the city. We will wrap up our day with a tour of the student farm at the UW Campus and a firing of the cob oven! We will make pizzas pot-luck style and share the treats we discovered at the farmer&#039;s market!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; **Please note, this visit can only accommodate a limited number of people, so RSVP&amp;rsquo;s are required. To RSVP for the visit, or to get more information, please email Teresa at &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;mailto:fjp@seattleglobaljustice.org&quot;&gt;fjp@seattleglobaljustice.org&lt;/a&gt;. We will send you directions and bike route details before the event, as well as information about what to bring. All activities will be appropriate for children and we can work out disability accommodations if needed. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[4X', ''),
(1817, 2455047, 2455047, '19:30:00', '21:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Defend the RNC 8 - Film screening and benefit ', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday, August 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;7:30pm&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Cascade People&#039;s Center&lt;br /&gt;309 Pontius Ave. North&lt;br /&gt;Seattle, WA 98109 &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Common Action Seattle invites you to a screening of &lt;em&gt;Terrorizing Dissent&lt;/em&gt;, a film documenting the criminalization of dissent at the Republican National Convention in Saint Paul, Minnesota during September 2008.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;The film features unforgettable historical footage, interviews with the RNC8 protest organizers who are now facing conspiracy charges, and footage from more than 40 cameras and journalists on the streets during the convention. See what really happened, see who ordered police violence and see how ordinary people were brutalized by riot cops.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt; The event will also feature a fun door prize raffle bonanza. All proceeds benefit the RNC 8 defense fund. Following the film, stay for a Q &amp; A session with RNC 8 member Luce Guillen-Givins on anarchist organizing, arrestee and prisoner support work and much more.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Bus Routes: 8, 25, 70-73, 74, 77, 79, 304, 317, 355, 377. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Cascade People&#039;s Center is wheelchair accessible.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For more information on the RNC 8, visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.msplinks.com/MDFodHRwOi8vd3d3LnJuYzgub3Jn&quot;&gt;http://www.rnc8.org&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For more info or to request on-site childcare, please call David at 206-909-1024&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
