(2033, 2455233, 2455233, '19:00:00', '23:00:00', 'Years', 1, 'Awesome Land: Women of Dirt ', 'Featuring the bicycle stylings of Tammy Donahugh, Stephanie Nychka, Cierra Smith, Emily Johnston, Lisa Myklak, Jill Kintner, Leana Gerrard, Dawn Cashen, Katrina Strand, Kathy Pruitt, and Darcy Turenne, Awesome Land: Women Of Dirt is a unique look into the world of Downhill Racing, Dirt Jumping and Freeriding. This film looks through the eyes of the wondrous women that have helped grow the sport of Gravity Mountain Biking with their strength and courage. Other mountain bike films have overlooked these vibrant and dedicated women but no longer!  &lt;em&gt;Awesome Land: Women Of Dirt &lt;/em&gt;celebrates the mountain bike while celebrating the women who love them. A beautiful and energetic film that opens a window into an awesome world. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;file:///Users/publicitydirector/Library/Caches/TemporaryItems/moz-screenshot-1.png&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;file:///Users/publicitydirector/Library/Caches/TemporaryItems/moz-screenshot.png&quot; /&gt; ', 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2034, 2455239, 2455239, '20:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Cris Cheek Live ', '&lt;p&gt;Feb 11&lt;/p&gt;  					 						 	                            	 		 	  	 		 	                         					 					 					 					 						 	                                        	 		 			 		 				&lt;p&gt;Co-Presented with University of Washington Bothell&lt;/p&gt; 		 		 			 		 	             					 					 					 					  					 					 					 					&lt;p&gt; 						 							Thursday, Feb 11 at 08:00PM&lt;br /&gt; 						&lt;/p&gt; 					 					 					 	                                 	 		 	  &lt;p&gt;Cris Cheek is a sound artist, poet, photographer, mixed-media practitioner and interdisciplinary performer. He will perform an evening of &amp;ldquo;live writing&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;performance writing&amp;rdquo; works for sound, text and video. Cheek writes that he &amp;ldquo;projects video about writing and gets in the way of his projections, tries to read the writing, toys with and enacts ideas of trying to read what we might be seeing and changes what is seen by doing so.&amp;rdquo; His work, indebted to the history of sound poetry, is highly improvisational and ephemeral. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;One of the works he will be presenting, the video-text-performance piece &amp;ldquo;monday morning quarterbacking &amp;lsquo;on&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;off&amp;rsquo; gods commons,&amp;rdquo; has appeared on many &amp;ldquo;best-of&amp;rdquo; 2009 lists for experimental poetics. He will also be presenting other short videos, live sound pieces and readings from his acclaimed new book &amp;ldquo;part: short life housing&amp;rdquo; (The Gig, Toronto, 2009).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1214&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2035, 2455248, 2455248, '23:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Serj Tankian – Elect the Dead Symphony ', '&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/images/uploaded_images/0000/4361/serjtankian_feature.jpg&quot; /&gt; 	 	 	    	 	   	  			 	   						  					 					 						 						 						&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1213&quot;&gt;Serj Tankian &amp;ndash; Elect the Dead Symphony&lt;/a&gt; 						 						 						&lt;p&gt;Feb 20&lt;/p&gt; 						&lt;p&gt;(Madsen Minax, U.S.A. / New Zealand, 2009, Beta-SP, 62 min)&lt;/p&gt; 						 						&lt;p&gt; 							 								&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;On March 16th, 2009, Serj Tankian, a Grammy Award winner and one of rock&amp;rsquo;s most unconventional frontmen, took the stage at the majestic Auckland Town Hall in New Zealand with the Auckland Philharmonia Orchestra to perform a very special orchestral interpretation of his critically acclaimed debut solo album &lt;em&gt;Elect the Dead&lt;/em&gt;. The dynamic one- off performance was recorded and filmed in HD by six cameras, and the   dramatic result has been captured in &lt;em&gt;Elect the Dead Symphony&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With the Auckland Philharmonia Orchestra at his side, Tankian&amp;rsquo;s epic songs and operatic vocals take on a whole new sense of grandeur when performed by a full 70-piece orchestra, while the film&amp;rsquo;s sweeping edits showcase the drama of the concert. This unique meshing of two very different musical worlds was a vision Tankian has long wanted to make a reality. What sets &lt;em&gt;Elect The Dead Symphony&lt;/em&gt; apart from other successful pairings between rock artists and orchestras is that Tankian specifically rearranged his songs to be performed with only orchestral instruments.&lt;/p&gt; 							 						 						&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1213&quot;&gt;More&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2036, 2455238, 2455238, '19:00:00', '22:30:00', 'Once', 0, 'Veracity! Free Show feat. Baby Birds Don&#039;t Drink Milk and optional $3 vegan meal ', '&lt;br /&gt;Veracity! is a free show in The Vera Project Art Gallery. Come listen to music and check out The Vera Project. There will also be a vegan dinner available for $3&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This month featuring: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Baby Birds Don&#039;t Drink Milk &lt;br /&gt;Big Dogs&lt;br /&gt;Emperor Moth&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hey friendlings,&lt;br /&gt;Yes, it&#039;s that time again! VERACITY! (!!!!!!!!) is here!&lt;br /&gt;So, in case you haven&#039;t already been to Veracity(!) yet, here&#039;s the scoop:&lt;br /&gt; &amp;bull; it&#039;s free. that&#039;s right, free.&lt;br /&gt; &amp;bull; there&#039;s great music. All performances for Veracity(!) take place in the gallery space of the Vera Project, not the main stage (read: intimate show)&lt;br /&gt; &amp;bull; there is an optional vegan meal ($3)&lt;br /&gt; &amp;bull; it&#039;s awesome to show up on time for this show. We try to run on real-world time, not punk rock time.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Specs for February 10th, 7pm&lt;br /&gt; Bands:&lt;br /&gt;    &amp;bull; Baby Birds Don&#039;t Drink Milk (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/babybirdsdontdrinkmilk&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/babybirdsdontdrinkmilk&lt;/a&gt;) - pretty mellow but with epic crescendoes thrown in! I&#039;m really excited about these folks. According to their myspace they play &quot;Melodramatic Popular Songs&quot; and they hail from CHOMP WOMP PIZZA CASTLE, United States. What&#039;s not to like???&lt;br /&gt;    &amp;bull; Big Dogs (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/bigdogs&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/bigdogs&lt;/a&gt;) - awesome fun and great songs by awesome fun and great youngsters, featuring members of kick ass seattle bands herr jazz and problems.&lt;br /&gt;    &amp;bull; Emperor Moth (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/emperormothmusic&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/emperormothmusic&lt;/a&gt;) - a sort of sound experiment from pdx. Nice vocals and a good back beat to bop around to. Don&#039;t miss this.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://i306.photobucket.com/albums/nn243/trisaratops08/FebVeracity.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;  ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(2037, 2455226, 2455226, '19:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Margaret Killjoy Reading at Left Bank Books! ', 'Come see Margaret Killjoy, author of Mythmakers and Lawbreakers: Anarchist Writers on Fiction, come speak tonight at Left Bank! It will be a real smash.  Come get involved in your local anarchist project! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Basically, &lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;anarchy&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt; is in fact the only political position that is actually possible.&amp;rdquo; -Alan Moore&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hope to see you there!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;3 Left Bankers ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
