(2171, 2455316, 2455316, '19:00:00', '23:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Queer Mixer at Watertown Coffee ', 'Type: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.facebook.com/search/?o&quot;&gt;Party&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.facebook.com/search/?o&quot;&gt;Mixer&lt;/a&gt;   Date: Thursday, April 29, 2010 Time: 7:05pm - 11:05pm Location: Watertown Coffee Street: 550 12th Ave  City/Town: Seattle, WA&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Queer Mixer at Watertown Coffee is an ALL AGES social event for all queer, trans, genderqueer, bi, intersex, lesbian, gay, questioning, heteroflexible, bicurious, queer-ish &amp; allied people. [additions welcome, if you don&#039;t see your identity here, just let us know!]&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Celebrate Spring!&lt;br /&gt;Spring Fever theme: dress appropriately. . .(and by that we mean appropriate to the theme of spring fever, which may be quite inappropriate according to some standards)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*FEATURING a special Spring Fever spoken word performance by &lt;br /&gt;Jessica McPherson*&lt;br /&gt;&amp;&lt;br /&gt;*STRIPPING by&lt;br /&gt;iL Nocturnal*&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come socialize, meet new folks, play ping pong, dance, etc!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Watertown Coffee is not just a coffee shop, there is a lovely selection of vegetarian and vegan dinner options, alcoholic drinks (with ID), coffee beverages of course, and a few random non caffeinated, non alcoholic options.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;find us on facebook:&lt;br /&gt;http://www.facebook.com/?ref=home#!/event.php?eid=108379692532057&amp;index=1 ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(2172, 2455330, 2455330, '20:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Caethua (Maine), St Rainbow, Thunder:Grey:Pilgrim and Cap Lori at the Office of Dr. Glorious ', '&lt;span&gt;I am really, truly and honestly excited for this show. It&#039;s going to be so amazing. Three of my favorite bands/groups of people and one band I have never heard but have heard good things about!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Caethua is coming from Maine. Caethua is the amazing Claire Hubbard. Her music is the very definition of haunting. She has a great voice and a great command of sound. &lt;br /&gt;http://www.myspace.com/caethua&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;St Rainbow is Garrett Kelly and Amber Kai Morgan. Together they founded the great and mighty Hollow Earth Radio. St Rainbow is an extension of the ideas they present via the radio. Really beautiful songs with all kinds of unexpected twists and turns. http://www.myspace.com/strainbow&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Thunder Grey Pilgrim is the magickal Mitchell. Ritualistic Drone that will shake you to your core and leave you wanting more. Truly earth shaking.&lt;br /&gt;http://www.myspace.com/thundergreypilgrim&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Then we have Cap Lori. I don&#039;t know much about them but I hear that Kaz from Pwrfl Pwr plays in it and the songs I have heard on the internets are quite hushed and lovely. http://www.myspace.com/caplori&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;What a great show!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The show will be starting sharply at 8pm because after 6 years of doing shows, we now have a crazy and irrational neighbor who likes to call the cops rather than have mature discussions so.....we are now trying to follow the legal rules but until 10 pm or so, we will happily annoy the heck out of her!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Also, be sure to bring some money to help Caethua get around this large country of ours. It&#039;s really important in these times to support our diy&#039;ing (that&#039;s DIY&#039;ing not dying) friends. If you can afford beer, you can afford to pay a few measly bucks for a really great show! &lt;/span&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
