(2221, 2455389, 2455389, '18:30:00', '23:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'THE STOLEN ORGAN FAMILY BAND, WEBELOS, WEHRWOLVE, BRAD DUNN @ The BREAD FACTORY ', '&lt;img src=&quot;http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4076/4740086905_a12c9a328f.jpg&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Grill up your favorite veggie or meat items. BBQ at 6:30 MUSIC starts at  7:30. This show MUST end by 11PM. We will also be celebrating Cat  Wilcox&#039;s Birthday!! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;WEBELOS (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/thewebelosmusic&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/thewebelosmusic&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;Blah,  Blah, Blah.... we all know how much The Bread Factory LOVES webelos.  This will be their third time playing here. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;THE STOLEN ORGAN  FAMILY BAND &lt;br /&gt;(&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Stolen-Organ-Family-Band/10481193227&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Stolen-Organ-Family-Band/10481193227&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;I  met Conor and Kelly on a mini tour with Dufus last year. They are  possibly the nicest folks. Trust me you will want to bring extra money  to pick up whatever they are selling.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;WEHRWOLVE  (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/wehrwolve&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/wehrwolve&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;The  unknown is often inherently scary; Wehrwolve explore mostly uncharted  aural territory, reveling in esoteric, ritualistic sounds that whisper  and chant of realms that are aeons beyond milquetoasty indie rock and  cozy folk strum-alongs. By contrast, Wehrwolve craft paganistic  excursions informed by drone, electronics, and chance operations. Where  are they going with this music? Hard to say, but it&amp;rsquo;s exhilaratingly  unsettling.&amp;rdquo; - Dave Segal, The Stranger&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;BRAD DUNN (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/modocos&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/modocos&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;Brad  is one of my favorite musicians alive. Come see him play on the 11th..  maybe with a brand new band... we can all help name the band. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
