(2254, 2455457, 2455463, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Bunny &amp; the Bull ', 'NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;            Normal   0   0   1   142   814   6   1   999   11.1287               0         0   0             &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SEPTEMBER 17&amp;ndash;23, FRIDAY&amp;ndash;THURSDAY AT 7 (PLUS SATURDAY &amp; SUNDAY AT 5PM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Seattle Premiere &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bunny &amp; The Bull&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Paul King, UK, 2010, 35mm, 101min)  &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Written and directed by &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Mighty Boosh&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; director Paul King, &lt;em&gt;Bunny and the Bull&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; is one of the most original and charismatic films to come out of Britain in recent years. Stephen Turnbull hasn&#039;t been outside in months. When a sudden infestation of mice forces him to abandon his routine, he finds his mind hurtling back to the eventful trek around Europe he undertook with his friend Bunny. Using whatever objects are within easy reach in Stephen&#039;s flat&amp;mdash;clay models, metallic gears and old souvenirs&amp;mdash;Stephen undertakes a surrealistic journey, paying homage to both the works of Michel Gondry, Terry Gilliam and Jean-Pierre Jeunet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&quot;King has the same kind of olde worlde, amateur-hour aesthetic as Wes Anderson and Michel Gondry, and his papier mâché/metalwork figures and landscapes are used to increasingly charming effect. &quot; &amp;mdash;This Is London&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;www.nwfilmforum.org&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2255, 2455456, 2455458, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Live at the Film Forum featuring THE FRENCH PROJECT ', 'NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;            Normal   0   0   1   129   738   6   1   906   11.1287               0         0   0             &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SEPTEMBER 16&amp;ndash;18, THURSDAY&amp;ndash;SATURDAY AT 8PM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LIVE AT THE FILM FORUM featuring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE FRENCH PROJECT: The New New Wave&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Seattle&amp;rsquo;s ridiculously bratty neo-French all-star music collective presents a new show incorporating the smuttiness of Gainsbourg, the existentialism of Godard and the absurd desperation of a band of people who can barely speak French or hang on to a day job. TFP plays music on unexpected instruments, ranging from Saint-Saëns and Debussy to Francoise Hardy and ZZ Top. Featuring secret guest appearances and short films by local notables including Tania Kupczak, Karn Junkinsmith and Richard Lefebvre. Complètement en français, bien sûr. Don&amp;rsquo;t forget your absinthe flask. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The French Project is&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;: Sara Edwards, Basil Harris, Erin Jorgensen and Charles Smith; with special appearances by Kirk Anderson on drums and Brendan Kellogg on cello.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;www.nwfilmforum.org&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;$12/Film Forum members, $15/general &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2256, 2455499, 2455505, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Howl ', 'NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;            Normal   0   0   1   110   628   5   1   771   11.1287               0         0   0             &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OCTOBER 29&amp;ndash;NOVEMBER 4, FRIDAY&amp;ndash;THURSDAY AT 7, 9PM (PLUS SATURDAY &amp; SUNDAY AT 5PM)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Presented by Northwest Film Forum and Earshot Jazz &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Howl&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Rob Epstein, Jeffrey Friedman, USA, 2010, 35mm, 90 min) &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;The beats are alive and well thanks to a soaring performance by &lt;strong&gt;James Franco&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; in &lt;em&gt;Howl&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;, a mesmerizing channeling of Allen Ginsberg, set in 1957 San Francisco as his poetic masterpiece is put on trial. Part hallucinatory animation, part courtroom drama, part period piece about the creation of the iconic beat poem and the censorship trial for obscenity that followed its 1956 City Lights publication, &lt;em&gt;Howl&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; is bred with unexpected life and energy. It affirms itself as a genre-bending hybrid that brilliantly captures a pivotal moment: the birth of a counterculture. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;www.nwfilmforum.org&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2257, 2455505, 2455505, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Do It Again ', 'NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;            Normal   0   0   1   140   803   6   1   986   11.1287               0         0   0             &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOVEMBER 4, THURSDAY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; &lt;strong&gt;AT 7, 9PM &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Seattle Premiere &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Sponsored by Easy Street Records&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do It Again&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Robert Patton Spruill, USA, 2010, DigiBeta, 90 min) &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Every serious music fan has a favorite band&amp;mdash;but it&amp;rsquo;s a very rare fan that single-handedly attempts to reunite that band years after they&amp;rsquo;ve packed it in. In order to conquer his midlife crisis, the committed pop journalist Geoff Edgers&amp;rsquo; dream is to bring back together &lt;strong&gt;The Kinks.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; After years of squabbling over creative differences, The Kinks founding brothers, Ray and Dave Davies, don&amp;rsquo;t speak to each other anymore. But Edgers remains undeterred, and he sets out on a quixotic quest to bring the brothers together again. Along the way, he receives advice from fellow Kinks fans like &lt;strong&gt;Sting, Peter Weller of the Jam, Peter Buck, Robyn Hitchcock, and Zooey Deschanel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;, all of whom he attempts to engage in a Kinks sing-a-long. &lt;em&gt;Do It Again&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt; is a fascinating document of the kind of music-loving mania embraced by all true fans. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;www.nwfilmforum.org&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2258, 2455513, 2455514, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Making Faces: Metal Type in the 21st Century ', 'NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;            Normal   0   0   1   106   607   5   1   745   11.1287               0         0   0             &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOVEMBER 12&amp;ndash;13, FRIDAY&amp;ndash;SATURDAY AT 7PM &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Seattle Premiere &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Director in attendance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;Presented by Northwest Film Forum and The School Of Visual Communications &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Making Faces: Metal Type in the 21st Century&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Richard Kegler, USA/France, 2005, 16mm, 103 min) &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;This fascinating design documentary captures the personality and work process of the late Canadian graphic artist Jim Rimmer (1931-2010). In 2008, P22 type foundry commissioned Rimmer to create a new type design (Stern) that became the first-ever simultaneous release of a digital font and hand-set metal font. Rimmer was one of only a few who possess the skills needed to create a metal font. This film is a unique opportunity to share Jim&amp;rsquo;s knowledge and processes with the world. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;www.nwfilmforum.org&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2259, 2455418, 2455418, '19:00:00', '22:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Open In-Studio Performances! ', 'Have  you always wanted to be part of a live studio audience? Now&#039;s yer  chance! Come check out Hollow Earth Radio&#039;s new station headquarters and  watch an in-studio interview/performance as it is broadcast LIVE!  Actually, come watch THREE in-studio visits by: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;7PM &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/lumpkinsband&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/lumpkinsband&lt;/a&gt; Lumpkins, visiting from  Bellingham. They&#039;ll be interviewed by The Corner Pocket&#039;s DJ Co-Pocket&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;8PM  LA&#039;s &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/mosescampbell&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/mosescam...pbell&lt;/a&gt; Moses Campbell, who&#039;ll be chatting with DJ  Garrett of the St Rainbow Show&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;9PM &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/cockandswan&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/cockandswan&lt;/a&gt; Cock &amp; Swan from nearby  Bothell, hosted by DJ Slashed Tires of Late Nights for the Longing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;2018A Union St in the Central District! ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(2260, 2455423, 2455423, '14:00:00', '18:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'WORKSHOPS! CIRCUIT BENDING + SEWING ', 'HER is hosting two workshops as part of our opening week events! &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Starting  at 2pm, learn how to craft your own instruments and noise makers out of  those dusty... old electronics laying around the house.  Bunker Kaziu, &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/bunkerkaziu&quot;&gt;www.myspace.com/bunkerkaziu&lt;/a&gt;, will show you how to &quot;bend&quot; the  circuit board into new ideas. This is a beginner&#039;s workshop, and if you  have your own toy or electronic piece bring it along. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Then at  4pm join us for Summer Jams and Jammies, an easy summer clothes sewing  workshop. We&amp;rsquo;ll listen to hot tunes suited for the hot weather while we  stitch up new duds. There will be plenty of fabric,  but bring your own if you have some!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;2018A Union St in the Central District! ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[5X', ''),
(2261, 2455423, 2455423, '19:00:00', '21:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Artist Reception: Live In the Pacific Northwest ', 'Over the first two months in Hollow Earth Radio&#039;s new space, our entry way will be filled  with hundreds of images Joseph captured of local bands doing their  thing on stage. Look out for pictures of the Pica Beats, Triumph of  Lethargy, Cold Lake, and Kimya Dawson among nearly every northwest band  you could... think of from recent years. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Join us  on the evening of August 14th for the opening of his work at our new  space!&lt;br /&gt;2018A Union St in the Central District ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2262, 2455423, 2455423, '21:00:00', '00:01:00', 'Once', 0, 'HER Celebration Concert ', 'Starting at 9pm the new Hollow Earth Radio studio will be turned into venue as we host a  kickoff show to bring the good vibes to our new space. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bring  your friends and dance your feet off all night to:&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Brain Fruit  -- &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/brainfruitmusic&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/brainfruitmusic&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Casual  Lust -- &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/thecasuallust&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/thecasuallust&lt;/a&gt; (This is their ONCE annual  show!)&lt;br /&gt;Kung Foo Grip -- &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/kungfoogripsucka&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/kungfoogripsucka&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is a free show,  but if you&amp;rsquo;re feeling generous, throw $5 into the donation jar  available. The live music begins with a screening of music videos  produced by our neighbors Reel Grrls.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;2018A Union St in the Central District&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(2263, 2455415, 2455415, '12:01:00', '13:15:00', 'Weeks', 1, 'Yoga for Bikers ', 'Riding bikes is the best way to get around town, but riding without stretching out can leave your muscles tight and sore. This engaging yoga class focuses on loosening up leg muscles and opening hips, while leaving your body balanced and open. I incorporate aspects of several yoga traditions, blending vinyasas, static poses and breathing. All levels welcome. Sliding Scale $10 @ Fremont Abbey, Trades Welcome&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Kelli Refer, RYT&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more information:http://yogaforbikers.wordpress.com ', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[2X', ''),
(2264, 2455416, 2455416, '19:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Hot Toddies @ Cafe Fusion ', '&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:lucidagrande,verdana,arial,sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:rgb(56,44,27);line-height:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Saturday, August 7th, indie surf pop darlings The Hot Toddies will be performing at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/fusioncafe&quot;&gt;Fusion Cafe&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;a little known, yet wonderful, all ages venue in the heart of downtown&lt;/strong&gt;! If you&amp;rsquo;re in the know, then you&amp;rsquo;ve already been here to see one of the numerous national touring artist that has performed here in the last year and a half. But if not, here is your chance!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For all you avid KEXP listeners our there, you&amp;rsquo;ll remember The Hot Toddies from back in 2007 when their last album was released and they got major airplay on the station. In fact, they even did a great live in-studio performance (that you can listen to &lt;a href=&quot;http://kexp.org/live/liveperformance.aspx?rID&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;). I think that the band&amp;rsquo;s bio gives the best description I have heard of them yet: &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Oakland&amp;rsquo;s sweethearts,&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;&quot;&gt;The Hot Toddies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;, mix 1950&amp;rsquo;s beach pop with indie rock riffs, a bottle of whiskey and a dry sense of humor.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Along with the &lt;em&gt;Toddies&lt;/em&gt;, a bunch of other great local bands will be performing. There will be great acoustic sets from &lt;strong&gt;Chris Crusher&lt;/strong&gt; (of Smokejumper, who were recently named one of the next 5 Seattle bands to get signed), &lt;strong&gt;Jefferson Death Star&lt;/strong&gt; (Ryan Koreski from the Damage Done, another band who was also on that list mentioned above), &lt;strong&gt;MT148&lt;/strong&gt; (melodic singer/songwriter indie with inspirations ranging from the Weakerthans and Apple Seed Cast to the Murder City Devils), and &lt;strong&gt;Arms Like Cables&lt;/strong&gt; (two guys playing together that sound like Chuck Ragan)! In short, it&amp;rsquo;s a show you don&amp;rsquo;t wanna miss. And do note&amp;hellip;IT STARTS EARLY! 7PM.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;So, be sure to come out out if you love bands that &amp;ldquo;[blend] 60&amp;rsquo;s pop, doo-wop, and beautiful harmonies,&amp;rdquo; or local music. Either way, you will not be disappointed!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Saturday, August 7th&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Hot Toddies (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/thehottoddies&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/thehottoddies&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;Chris Crusher (of Smokejumper)&lt;br /&gt;Jefferson Death Star (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/therealjeffersondeathstar&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/therealjeffersondeathstar&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;MT148 (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.myspace.com/mt148&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.myspace.com/mt148&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br /&gt;Arms Like Cables&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;@ The Fusion Cafe (909 4th Ave)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;&quot;&gt;$6 &amp;ndash; 7PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(2265, 2455431, 2455431, '17:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Super Secret folk-punk Mini-Fest @ THE BRIDGE TO NOWHERE w/ Jessie Williams, Junk Bones, More TBA! ', 'its the end of the anarchist bookfair weekend!  what better way to celebrate than by having a rad show in the park!  there will be a ton of awesome folky-punky musicians playing and maybe even some delicious vegan food?  its gonna be fun, but only if youre there too!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;we are not officially affiliated with the anarchist bookfair or its organizers, we are just friends and supporters of the bookfair who wanted to out put on  show.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;do YOU want to play?  contact Junk Bones (sidewalkcracks [at] riseup.net) and well work it out!  acoustic only, no amplification (sadly).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Sun Aug 22nd, 5PM @ The Bridge to Nowhere&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Jessie Williams (oakland) http://www.myspace.com/thesuburbanrevolt&lt;br /&gt;Junk Bones (seattle) http://www.myspace.com/junkbones&lt;br /&gt;Todi Stronghangs (canada) http://www.myspace.com/todistronghands&lt;br /&gt;Beat Alice (oregon) http://www.myspace.com/marylove136669&lt;br /&gt;MORE TBA!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;see you there! ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
