(2286, 2455450, 2455450, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Balkan Dance Party w/DJ Joro Boro, Lache Cercel &amp; The Roma Swing Ensemble, and Bucharest Drinking Team ', '&lt;br /&gt;--Balkan Dance Party: September 10--&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;DJ Joro Boro&lt;br /&gt;Bulgarian Etnotek via New York&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Lache Cercel &amp; The Roma Swing Ensemble&lt;br /&gt;Red-Hot Romanian Roma Rampage&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bucharest Drinking Team&lt;br /&gt;Eastern Bloc Party Music&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Friday September 10,&lt;br /&gt;Doors at 7:30/Show at 8pm&lt;br /&gt;Tickets: $10/adv, $15/door&lt;br /&gt;http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/126107&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hale&#039;s Palladium&lt;br /&gt;4301 Leary Way NW&lt;br /&gt;Seattle, WA 98107 &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;http://www.hearthmusic.com/concerts.html&lt;br /&gt;http://www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=123369264378317&amp;ref=ts &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Contact :&lt;br /&gt;devon@hearthmusic.com&lt;br /&gt;206-227-7622     &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;ALL-AGES, Drink w/ID&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Time for some of that Shaolin iron-liver training, cause this Eastern European party will test your limits of dancing, drinking and partying! Fresh off his DJ sets at Burning Man, DJ Joro Boro is known for his intense mash-ups of Balkan horns, accordions and songs with blazing drum &#039;n bass beats. His music laid the groundwork for the New York gypsy music of Gogol Bordello and Balkan Beat Box, and has fueled many all-night parties in New York&#039;s Bulgarian and Balkan immigrant communities (and hipsters). He&#039;ll be joined by master Romanian fiddler Lache Cercel and his Roma Swing Ensemble and Seattle&#039;s premier Balkan party band, The Bucharest Drinking Team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;BIOS:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;DJ Joro Boro&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Former resident of the legendary Mehanata Bulgarian Bar in New York, Joro-Boro plays and promotes etnoteck - the dirty and uninhibited side of globalization as a forced feed back into a party without borders, a three-day Balkan wedding in a post-national state where noise, bass and desire detonate the conglomerate monoculture. He is a monthly host of MoGlo (Modern Global) on Radio New York (KEXP), has toured with Balkan Beat Box, and has performed with artists ranging from Bassnectar to Tinariwen.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Lache Cercel &amp; The Roma Swing Ensemble&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Lache Cercel was one of the finest violinists in Romania before he left his home country to emigrate to Western Canada. Now living in British Columbia, he has absorbed the cosmopolitan nfluences of Vancouver&#039;s urban streets, and mixed his new love for jazz and swing with the red-hot blazing fiddling so commonly associated with Romanian&#039;s Roma (Gypsy) communities. Lache&#039;s band blends the swing of Vancouver&#039;s black-tie jazz clubs with technically dazzling Balkan folk music in a range of difficult time signatures. It&#039;s a fresh, new sound from our Northern neighbors and a chance to dance to some of the smoothest Balkan music you&#039;ve ever heard.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bucharest Drinking Team&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Bucharest Drinking Team isn&#039;t just a professional competitive liquor disposal club. It&#039;s also an ensemble of fine musicians, with high-proof, anise-scented dance tunes specially distilled for your Eastern Bloc party. The first-string vocal squad is backed by a traditional Romanian taraf midfield team and an impenetrable brass defense line. From its eastern-European home field, the team&#039;s musical repertory also travels to exhibition tunes from other drinking leagues in Europe and North America. ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(2287, 2455459, 2455459, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, '2010 Pike Place Market Buskers Festival ', 'Announcing the 2010 Pike Place Market Buskers&#039; Festival&lt;br /&gt;Sunday, September 19 / 11:00 AM - 5:00 PM&lt;br /&gt;On the Streets and Alleys of the Pike Place Market&amp;hellip; FREE&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The 9th annual Pike Place Market Buskers&amp;rsquo; Festival is a full-day celebration of the Northwest&amp;rsquo;s finest street performers. The buskers make the streets their stage every day, rain or shine, and are a key part of the Market&amp;rsquo;s culture. These master performers have a variety of talents: a cappella singers, balloon twisters,&lt;br /&gt;guitarists, mandolinists, magicians, trombonists, harmonica players, accordionists and erhu players, but they&#039;re all united by their desire to bring art out of the concert halls and into the street. Join the Pike Place Market Performers&#039; Guild and 35+ street performers at the 2010 Pike Place Market Buskers&amp;rsquo; Festival for a celebration of the Market&amp;rsquo;s culture. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At the 2010 Festival, many favorite market performers will be featured, like gospel quartet A Moment in Time and the ukulele crooning of Howlin&#039; Hobbit, and expect surprises from newly arrived buskers like old-timey banjo songster Gregory Paul and harmonic folk duo The Gloria Darlings. You can even some great magic tricks from Acep Hale! Enjoy witty and sentimental songs by Greg Spence Wolf, smokin&amp;rsquo; harmonica playing from Sleepy Joe, The 1 Knight Stand One Man Band, and the wit and wisdom of Mariide. These and many more performers will be featured on stage, so come down to check out all the artistic talent the Market has to offer.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With two amplified stages on Pike St and one acoustic stage in Post Alley, over 35 performers will be featured at the festival and crowds of 5,000 are expected to visit the market for the festival. For one day, the buskers will take over the market to showcase their diverse talents. A family-friendly and FREE event, come celebrate Pike Place Market and all the buskers that make it such a unique place to visit and enjoy.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To reach the Guild for comments or questions:&lt;br /&gt;Pike Place Market Performers&#039; Guild&lt;br /&gt;pmpgbuskers@gmail.com&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;============================================&lt;br /&gt;2010 Pike Place Buskers&amp;rsquo; Festival Lineup and Schedule&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;North Stage&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;11:00 Hua Zi  (Chinese erhu)&lt;br /&gt;11:30 Nicholas Rideout (Guitar, Vocals, Harmonica)&lt;br /&gt;12:00 Gary Ollinger Sonny Bono tribute&lt;br /&gt;12:30 dag (Too Much Variety, Blues Likely)&lt;br /&gt;1:00 Greg Spence Wolf (Sensitive and Silly Songs)&lt;br /&gt;1:30 Acep Hale (Magic, Mentalism and Escape)&lt;br /&gt;2:00 Pickled Okra  (An American Treasure)&lt;br /&gt;2:30 Blues Abusers (Blues to the Nth Degree)&lt;br /&gt;3:00 Gregory Paul (Old-Time Banjo and Singing)&lt;br /&gt;3:30 Morrison Boomer (2 Guitars)&lt;br /&gt;4:00 A Moment in Time (A Cappella Singers)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;South Stage&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;11:00 pkdwyer (Cosmic American Blues)&lt;br /&gt;11:30 Aeon Now (Dreampunk Roadside Cabaret)&lt;br /&gt;12:00 Hanging Chad (Acoustic Guitar, Bass and Percussion)&lt;br /&gt;12:30 Howlin Hobbit (Jazz and Novelty on Ukulele)&lt;br /&gt;1:00 Sleepy Joe (Blues, Rhythm &amp; Blues Harmonica)&lt;br /&gt;1:30 Mongrel Jews (3 Piece Banjo Mando)&lt;br /&gt;2:00 Snake Suspenderz (Hot Jazz Hokum and Novelty Music)&lt;br /&gt;2:30 Joel Blackstone (Acoustic Guitar and Vocals)&lt;br /&gt;3:00 Whitney Mouge (Singer, Songwriter, Guitar, Acoustic Soul)&lt;br /&gt;3:30 Shawn McCole and friends (Jug Band Extraordinaire)&lt;br /&gt;4:00 The Gloria Darlings (Female Indie Folk-Grass Duet)&lt;br /&gt;4:30 SmallTime String Band (Four Piece Family Band, Old-Timey Originals)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Post Alley&lt;br /&gt;11:00 Tommy Dean (One Man Band, Very Entertaining)&lt;br /&gt;11:30 Scott Free (Sing, Play Guitar)&lt;br /&gt;12:00 Brother Willie (A Cappella Singer)&lt;br /&gt;12:30 Dandelion Junk Queens (Accordion &amp; Saw &amp; Singing Ladies)&lt;br /&gt;1:00 Craig Lay (The Awesome Power of Rock &amp; Roll)&lt;br /&gt;1:30 Mariide (Wit and Wisdom)&lt;br /&gt;2:00 Twister Thomas (Twist Tie Novelty Balloon Creations)&lt;br /&gt;2:30 Jeanne Towne (Autoharp and Vocals)&lt;br /&gt;3:00 Emilio Rodenas (Singing with Guitar Accompaniment)&lt;br /&gt;3:30 James Coates (Vocals, Guitar, Harmonica, Family Friendly)&lt;br /&gt;4:00 Briggs (Sing and Play Guitar)&lt;br /&gt;4:30 Joe Doney (1 Knight Stand One Man Band) ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', '');
