(2290, 2455479, 2455479, '10:00:00', '14:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Volunteer on the Duwamish River! ', '&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial,sans-serif;font-size:13px;border-collapse:collapse;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;Hello all!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;Twice a year, EOS Alliance partners with the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.duwamishcleanup.org/index.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,110,171);&quot;&gt;Duwamish River Cleanup Coalition&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pugetsound.org/events/duwamishalive&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,110,171);&quot;&gt;People for Puget Sound&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to host one of Seattle&amp;rsquo;s largest environmental stewardship events, &amp;ldquo;&lt;a href=&quot;http://duwamishalive.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,110,171);&quot;&gt;Duwamish Alive!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rdquo; With events all over Seattle and surrounding communities there&#039;s bound to be one near you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;The EOS Alliance, in partnership with CleanScapes sponsors and hosts volunteers at a cleanup site located at Gateway Park on 8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:small;&quot;&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; Ave S, in Georgetown. Coupling the mission of EOS Alliance we encourage a zero waste policy and will have recycling and composting facilities at all cleanup sites along the Duwamish River.  With members of the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.georgetownneighborhood.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,110,171);&quot;&gt;Georgetown Community Council&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and CleanScapes, on Oct 9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:small;&quot;&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; we&amp;rsquo;ll be rolling up our sleeves to plant native species, eradicate invasives and pick up trash along the river.  There will &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;free food, both breakfast and lunch,&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and hopefully some late fall sunshine.  &lt;strong&gt;SAVE THE DATE!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;When: Sat, Oct 9, 10am-2pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;Where: Gateway Park (South end of 8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:small;&quot;&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; Ave S)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;Who: EOS employees, family, friends, community members&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;What: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;Plant&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;native species, pull up weeds and invasive species, pick up litter, and EAT DELICIOUS LUNCH!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;Read on for more about the fascinating Duwamish River:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;The Duwamish River has been heavily polluted for over 100 years by industry along the shore. Toxins in the Duwamish include PCBs, Lead, Mercury, Phalates and a long list of other chemicals dumped or buried in the river sediments (many of which are cancerous). Negligent and ignorant practices along the shore went on for decades before the EPA stepped in. In 2001, the River was declared a Superfund site&amp;mdash;one of the most polluted sites in the country&amp;mdash;and a plan was implemented to begin restoration. Only 2% of the original Duwamish wetlands exist today and while we can&amp;rsquo;t expect to completely restore the original habitats of the Duwamish, steps are being taken to cleanup toxins and create a healthier environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;For more information or to find an event in your area visit: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.duwamishalive.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Duwamish Alive!&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;To RSVP contact &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:tflynn@eosalliance.org&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;tflynn@eosalliance.org&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:arial;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[9X', ''),
(2291, 2455466, 2455466, '16:00:00', '21:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'SeattlePunk.Org BLOCK PARTY 2010! ', 'It&#039;s that time again... Get ready for the SPO Block Party 2010!!! &lt;br /&gt;This is an early show on Sunday afternoon 9/26/2010 starting at 4pm featuring: Mind Candy, Spinal Cracker, Steelhorse and Potty Mouth Society&lt;br /&gt;It is at The Morgue in Georgetown (5901 Airport Way S. Seattle, WA) &lt;br /&gt;All Ages, BYOB with ID. It is also a potluck so if you want to bring some food to share, feel free!&lt;br /&gt;$6 suggested donation.&lt;br /&gt;This a benefit show for SeattlePunk.Org, a fantastic website supporting independant music in the Seatle area and beyond with a concert calendar and open forums to discuss all kinds of things pertaining to punk music and culture as well as lots of other random stuff. Please check it out if you haven&#039;t yet. &lt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.seattlepunk.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#3b5998&quot;&gt;www.seattlepunk.org&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Come on out and help support your local scene!&lt;br /&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;http://sphotos.ak.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ak-ash2/hs332.ash2/61263_437419187972_716617972_4926091_1745918_n.jpg&quot; /&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
