(2306, 2455499, 2455499, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Friday: October 29th. An evening of mystery, spooks and creeps at Hollow Earth Radio! ', 'Join us at the new Hollow Earth Radio station for a spooktacular night of creeps. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will answer the question: What happens when you put 10 pounds of dry ice into a bowl of water?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Let your eyes and ears feast on the first performance of local creeps, Scorpio Scorpio Scorpio. &lt;br /&gt;A subtle scream, the cutting shrill of wine glasses, and a bowed guitar. Beacon hill represent. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Witness the terror of Spencer Moody, dressed as a handsome sailor, playing songs for children. &lt;br /&gt;(note: songs are probably not suitable for children) &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you aren&#039;t entertained by the local talent, bring a pillow, toke the toke and come watch &lt;br /&gt;Snakes on a Plane being projected during the show. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Show starts at 8pm and we are taking donations at the door. &lt;br /&gt;(!) Free candy (!) with a 5$ donation. &lt;br /&gt;All-ages, no booze, no jerks. &lt;br /&gt;2018 A E. Union St. in the Central District next to 2020 cycle.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://yourheartbreaks.com/HER/spookyflyer_smallest.jpg&quot; /&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
(2308, 2455534, 2455540, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Strange Powers: Stephin Merritt and the Magnetic Fields ', '&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/images/uploaded_images/0000/6441/stephin_feature.jpg&quot; /&gt; 	 	 	    	 	   	  			 	   						  					 					 						&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/programs/69&quot;&gt;Music Movies&lt;/a&gt; 						 						&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1596&quot;&gt;Strange  Powers: Stephin Merritt and the Magnetic Fields&lt;/a&gt; 						&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sponsored by &lt;a href=&quot;http://easystreetonline.com/&quot;&gt;Easy Street Records&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong /&gt; 						 						&lt;p&gt;Dec 10 - Dec 16&lt;/p&gt; 						&lt;p&gt;(Kerthy Fix and Gail O&amp;rsquo;Hara, USA, 2010, HD, 82 min) &lt;/p&gt; 						 						&lt;p&gt; 							 								&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strange Powers&lt;/em&gt; draws on co-director and fan Gail  O&amp;rsquo;Hara&amp;rsquo;s ten years of filming the band, creating an intimate portrait  of Merritt, the man and the songwriter. The film, cleanly and forcefully  shot by Paul Kloss is expertly recorded and mixed to showcase the  remarkable range of acoustic instruments used by the band.&lt;/p&gt; 							 						 						&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1596&quot;&gt;More&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 					 					  ', 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2309, 2455218, 2455224, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'Enemies of the People ', '&lt;strong&gt;NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; 			 				 			 					 						 						 						 	 	  	  	&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/images/uploaded_images/0000/6401/enemies2_rgb_m_feature.jpg&quot; /&gt; 	 	 	    	 	   	  			 	   						  					 					 						 						 						&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1605&quot;&gt;Enemies  of the People&lt;/a&gt; 						&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seattle Premiere! &lt;br /&gt; Sponsored by &lt;a href=&quot;http://kbcs.fm/&quot;&gt;KBCS 91.3FM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong /&gt; 						 						&lt;p&gt;Jan 21 - Jan 27, 2011&lt;/p&gt; 						&lt;p&gt;(Rob Lemkin &amp; Thet Sambath, 2010, UK/Cambodia, 35mm, 94  min.)&lt;/p&gt; 						 						&lt;p&gt; 							 								&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;One of the most harrowing and compelling personal  documentaries of our time, &lt;em&gt;Enemies of The People&lt;/em&gt;  exposes for the first time the truth about the Killing Fields and the  Khmer Rouge who were behind Cambodia&amp;rsquo;s genocide.&lt;/p&gt; 							 						 						&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1605&quot;&gt;More&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[8X', ''),
(2310, 2455238, 2455238, '00:00:00', '00:00:00', 'Once', 0, 'You&#039;re Lookin&#039; At Country ', 'NORTHWEST FILM FORUM PRESENTS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; 			 				 			 					 						 						 						 	 	  	  	&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/images/uploaded_images/0000/6466/five_minutes_to_live_feature.jpg&quot; /&gt; 	 	 	    	 	   	  			 	   						  					 					 						&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/programs/69&quot;&gt;Music Movies&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/programs/68&quot;&gt;Special Guests&lt;/a&gt; 						 						&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1611&quot;&gt;You&#039;re  Lookin&#039; At Country&lt;/a&gt; 						&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;Co-presented by American Standard Time&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Live guest performance!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 						 						&lt;p&gt;Feb 10, 2011&lt;/p&gt; 						&lt;p&gt;(Bill Karn, USA, 1961, DVD, 80 min)&lt;/p&gt; 						 						&lt;p&gt; 							 								&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For our 4th annual country program, &lt;strong&gt;Greg  Vandy &lt;/strong&gt;of KEXP&amp;rsquo;s The Roadhouse and American Standard  Time will host a jailhouse tour of desperate and dangerous men. The  evening&amp;rsquo;s lineup will include a surprise guest performance, forgotten  footage of vintage country performers singing tales of murder, mischief  and untimely death, and a rare screening of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Five Minutes to Live&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;,  starring the Man in Black, &lt;strong&gt;Johnny Cash&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; 							 						 						&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1611&quot;&gt;More&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; ', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '0[3X', ''),
